cs Circle]]\n| [[London Film Critics Circle Awards 1998#British Supporting Actress of the Year|British Supporting Actress of the Year]] <small>(tied with [[Minnie Driver]])</small>\n| ''The Last Days of Disco''\n| {{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2W2QCwAAQBAJ&pg=PP7&lpg=PP7&dq=kate+beckinsale+london+critics+circle+last+days+of+disco&source=bl&ots=tPkAiC7kiS&sig=JaWW1wVOqL8ewNk46wQ6Z6qAFlA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiv1cSGw-PMAhXJrY8KHbJ9BmMQ6AEIOTAG#v=onepage&q=kate%20beckinsale%20london%20critics%20circle%20last%20days%20of%20disco&f=false|title=Celebrity Biographies \u2013 The Amazing Life Of Kate Beckinsale|last=Green|first=Matt|publisher=Matt Green}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2002\n| [[MTV Movie Awards]]\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best Performance|Best Performance - Female]]\n| ''Pearl Harbor''\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Saturn Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Saturn Award for Best Actress#2000s|Best Actress]]\n| ''Serendipity''\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"china\">{{cite news|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/showbiz/2009-11/04/content_8913819.htm|title=Kate Beckinsale|work=[[China Daily]]|date=4 November 2009|accessdate=18 May 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160610104321/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/showbiz/2009-11/04/content_8913819.htm|archive-date=10 June 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''Underworld''\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"china\"/>\n|-\n| 2005\n| [[Screen Actors Guild]]\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture#2000s|Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture]] (shared with rest of cast)\n| ''The Aviator''\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"china\"/>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2006\n| [[MTV Movie Awards]]\n| [[2006 MTV Movie Awards#Best Hero|Best Hero]]\n| ''Underworld: Evolution''\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"china\"/>\n|-\n| [[People's Choice Awards]]\n| [[33rd People's Choice Awards|Favorite Female Action Star]]\n|\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"china\"/>\n|-\n| 2008\n| [[Broadcast Film Critics Association]]\n| [[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Actress#2000s|Best Actress]]\n| ''Nothing But the Truth''\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"china\"/>\n|-\n| 2012\n| [[Spike Guys' Choice Awards]]\n| [[Spike Guys' Choice Awards#2012 Awards|Jean-Claude Gahd Dam]]\n| ''Underworld: Awakening''\n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=\"china\"/>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2016\n| [[Gotham Awards]]\n| [[Gotham Independent Film Awards 2016#Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n| rowspan=\"4\"| ''Love & Friendship''\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| [[Critics' Choice Movie Awards|Critics Choice Awards]]\n| [[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Actress in a Comedy|Best Actress in a Comedy]]\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2017\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[London Critics Circle]]\n| [[London Film Critics' Circle Award for Actress of the Year]]\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| [[London Film Critics Circle Award for British Actress of the Year]]\n| {{won}}\n|\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{commons category|Kate Beckinsale}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=0000295}}\n* {{Tcmdb name}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://ftvdb.bfi.org.uk/sift/individual/325721 |title=Beckinsale, Kate |publisher=[[British Film Institute]] Film & TV Database <!-- |accessdate=19 May 2012 -->}}\n* {{AllRovi person|4911|Kate Beckinsale}}\n* {{people.com|kate_beckinsale|Kate Beckinsale}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Awards for Kate Beckinsale\n|list =\n{{London Film Critics Circle Award for British Actress of the Year}}\n{{London Film Critics Circle Award for British Supporting Actress of the Year}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Beckinsale, Kate}}\n[[Category:1973 births]]\n[[Category:Actresses from London]]\n[[Category:Alumni of New College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:English expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:English film actresses]]\n[[Category:English people of Burmese descent]]\n[[Category:English television actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People educated at Godolphin and Latymer School]]\n[[Category:People from Chiswick]]\n[[Category:20th-century English actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century English actresses]]\n[[Category:English stage actresses]]\n[[Category:English radio actresses]]\n[[Category:English voice actresses]]\n[[Category:English video game actresses]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|British actress}}\n{{EngvarB|date=December 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Good article}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Kate Beckinsale\n| image              = Kate Beckinsale 2011 Comic-Con (truer color).jpg\n| caption            = Beckinsale at the 2011 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]\n| birth_name         = Kathrin<!-- \"Kathrin\" is correct, as listed on British birth records --> Romary<!-- \"Romary\" is correct, as listed on British birth records --> Beckinsale\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1973|7|26|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[Chiswick]], [[London]], England\n| occupation         = Actress\n| nationality        = [[English people|English]]\n| years_active       = 1991\u2013present\n| partner            = [[Michael Sheen]] (1995\u20132003)\n| spouse             = {{marriage|[[Len Wiseman]]|9 May 2004|5 November 2019|reason=divorced}}\n| parents            = [[Richard Beckinsale]]<br>[[Judy Loe]]\n| alma_mater         = [[New College, Oxford]]\n| children           = 1\n| relatives          = {{ubl|[[Samantha Beckinsale]] (half-sister)|[[Roy Battersby]] (stepfather)}}\n}}\n\n'''<!--- \"Kathrin Romary\" is correct, as listed on (British) birth records --->Kathrin Romary<!--- \"Kathrin Romary\" is correct, as listed on (British) birth records ---> Beckinsale''' (born 26 July 1973)<ref name=biography.com>{{cite web|url=https://www.biography.com/people/kate-beckinsale-20702025|title=Kate Beckinsale: Actress, Film Actress, Film Actor/Film Actress (1973\u2013)|website=[[Biography.com]]|publisher=[[A&E Networks]]|accessdate=28 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190129010128/https://www.biography.com/people/kate-beckinsale-20702025|archive-date=29 January 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> is an English actress. After some minor television roles, her film debut was ''[[Much Ado About Nothing (1993 film)|Much Ado About Nothing]]'' (1993) while a student at the [[University of Oxford]]. She appeared in British [[costume drama]]s such as ''[[Prince of Jutland]]'' (1994), ''[[Cold Comfort Farm (film)|Cold Comfort Farm]]'' (1995), ''[[Emma (1996 TV film)|Emma]]'' (1996), and ''[[The Golden Bowl (film)|The Golden Bowl]]'' (2000), in addition to various stage and radio productions. She started film work in the United States in the late 1990s, and, after appearing in small-scale dramas ''[[The Last Days of Disco]]'' (1998) and ''[[Brokedown Palace]]'' (1999), she starred in the war drama ''[[Pearl Harbor (film)|Pearl Harbor]]'' (2001), the [[romantic comedy]] ''[[Serendipity (film)|Serendipity]]'', and ''[[Tiptoes]]'' (2003). She followed those with appearances in ''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]'' (2004) and ''[[Click (2006 film)|Click]]'' (2006).\n\nAfter her role as [[Selene (Underworld)|Selene]] in the [[Underworld (film series)|''Underworld'' film series]] (2003\u20132016), Beckinsale is known for her work in action films, including ''[[Van Helsing (film)|Van Helsing]]'' (2004), ''[[Whiteout (2009 film)|Whiteout]]'' (2009), ''[[Contraband (2012 film)|Contraband]]'' (2012), and ''[[Total Recall (2012 film)|Total Recall]]'' (2012). She continues to make appearances in smaller dramatic projects such as ''[[Snow Angels (film)|Snow Angels]]'' (2007), ''[[Nothing but the Truth (2008 American film)|Nothing but the Truth]]'' (2008), and ''[[Everybody's Fine (2009 film)|Everybody's Fine]]'' (2009). In 2016, she received critical acclaim for her performance in the period comedy film ''[[Love & Friendship]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nKathrin Romary Beckinsale was born on 26 July 1973, in [[Chiswick]], [[London Borough of Hounslow|Borough of Hounslow]], London, England.<ref name=freeBMD>{{cite web|url=http://www.freebmd.org.uk/cgi/information.pl?cite=T1rGIUaacQU1NQH3SidTMA&scan=1|title=Civil Registration: Birth Registered in July, August and September 1973|accessdate=2 April 2016|website=FreeBMD.org.uk|publisher=Free UK Genealogy CIO}}</ref><ref name=birth>{{citation|title=Births, Marriages & Deaths Index of England & Wales, 1916\u20132005|via=[[Ancestry.com]]}} {{subscription}}</ref> She is the only child of actors [[Richard Beckinsale]] and [[Judy Loe]].<ref name=\"facingup\">{{cite news |title=Facing up to the past |first=Janie |last=Lawrence |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/opinion/facing-up-to-the-past-1265195.html |newspaper=The Independent |date=5 April 1997 |accessdate=5 October 2011 |location=London |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120130233803/http://www.independent.co.uk/opinion/facing-up-to-the-past-1265195.html |archive-date=30 January 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> She has an older paternal half-sister, actress [[Samantha Beckinsale]], but they are not in regular contact.<ref name=\"facingup\"/> Her father was of one quarter [[Bamar|Burmese]] descent.<ref name=\"TelegraphMag2004-04-25\">{{cite news |last=Mitchison |first=Amanda |title=Beast in the beauty |date=25 April 2004 |newspaper=Telegraph Magazine |url=http://www.theage.com.au/articles/2004/04/24/1082719677731.html |accessdate=28 July 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101005111348/http://www.theage.com.au/articles/2004/04/24/1082719677731.html |archive-date=5 October 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref> She made her first television appearance at the age of four, in an episode of ''[[This Is Your Life (UK TV series)|This is Your Life]]'' dedicated to her father.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Iyq1JPOJ-2k |title=Kate talks about dad Richard Beckinsale (UK interview) |accessdate=5 October 2011 |via=YouTube |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009204055/http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Iyq1JPOJ-2k |archive-date=9 October 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> When she was five years old, her 31-year-old father died suddenly of a [[heart attack]]. Beckinsale was deeply traumatised by the loss and \"started expecting bad things to happen.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/kate_beckinsale |title=Celebrity Central: Kate Beckinsale |accessdate=5 October 2011 |work=People |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110926125326/http://www.people.com/people/kate_beckinsale |archive-date=26 September 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"facingup\"/> Her widowed mother moved in with director [[Roy Battersby]] when Beckinsale was nine and she was brought up alongside his four sons and daughter.<ref>{{cite news |title=A weight off her mind: Kate Beckinsale |first=Jane|last=Wheatley |url=http://women.timesonline.co.uk/tol/life_and_style/women/celebrity/article1704594.ece |date=26 April 2007 |accessdate=5 October 2011 |newspaper=[[The Times]] |location=London, England}}</ref> She has a close relationship with her step-father,<ref name=\"facingup\"/> who was a member of the [[Workers Revolutionary Party (UK)|Workers Revolutionary Party]] during her youth.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2016/may/19/kate-beckinsale-phones-tapped-jane-austen-love-friendship|title=Kate Beckinsale: 'Our phones were tapped by spooks when we were growing up'|first=John|last=Patterson|date=19 May 2016|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|location=London, England|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603130732/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2016/may/19/kate-beckinsale-phones-tapped-jane-austen-love-friendship|archive-date=3 June 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Beckinsale helped to sell ''[[The News Line]]'', a [[Trotskyism|Trotskyist]] newspaper, as a little girl and has said the household phone was tapped following Battersby's blacklisting by the [[BBC]].<ref name=\"auto\"/> Family friends included [[Ken Loach]] and [[Vanessa Redgrave]].<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\nBeckinsale was educated at [[Godolphin and Latymer School]], an independent school for girls in [[Hammersmith]], [[West London]] and was involved with the [[Orange Tree Theatre|Orange Tree Youth Theatre]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.americanwaymag.com/london-oxford-university-kate-beckinsale-food |title=London Calling |accessdate=5 October 2011 |work=American Way |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928163109/http://www.americanwaymag.com/london-oxford-university-kate-beckinsale-food |archivedate=28 September 2011 |df= }}</ref> She was twice a winner of the [[WH Smith Literary Award|WH Smith Young Writers Award]] for both fiction and poetry.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/1364101.stm|title=Kate Beckinsale: English pearl|date=1 June 2001|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160710052334/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/1364101.stm|archive-date=10 July 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> She has described herself as a \"late bloomer\": \"All of my friends were kissing boys and drinking cider way before me. I found it really depressing that we weren't making camp fires and everyone was doing stuff like that.\"<ref name=\"fear\">{{cite news |title=Kate Beckinsale: No fear of flying |first=Tiffany |last=Rose |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/kate-beckinsale-no-fear-of-flying-754437.html |newspaper=The Independent |date=17 December 2004 |accessdate=5 October 2011 |location=London}}{{dead link|date=November 2011}}</ref> She had a nervous breakdown and developed [[Anorexia nervosa|anorexia]] at the age of 15<ref name=\"dad-confused-with-God\"/> and underwent [[Freudian]] [[psychoanalysis]] for four years.<ref name=\"facingup\"/>\n\nBeckinsale read [[French literature|French]] and [[Russian literature]] at [[New College, Oxford|New College]], [[University of Oxford|Oxford]], and was later described by a contemporary, journalist [[Victoria Coren Mitchell]], as \"whip-clever, slightly nuts, and very charming\".<ref>{{cite news |title=God bless Kate&nbsp;\u2014 better late than never |first=Victoria |last=Coren |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2005/jan/09/features.review |newspaper=The Observer |date=9 January 2005 |accessdate=5 October 2011 |location=London |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131221035333/http://www.theguardian.com/film/2005/jan/09/features.review |archive-date=21 December 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> She became friends with\n[[Roy Kinnear]]'s daughter Kirsty.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.express.co.uk/celebrity-news/746263/Kate-Beckinsale-recalls-father-s-soul-destroying-death|title=Kate Beckinsale recalls father's 'soul-destroying' death as she jokes of 'dead dads' club'|first=Kayleigh|last=Giles|date=22 December 2016|website=Daily Express|accessdate=30 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830075431/https://www.express.co.uk/celebrity-news/746263/Kate-Beckinsale-recalls-father-s-soul-destroying-death|archive-date=30 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> She was involved with the [[Oxford University Dramatic Society]], most notably being directed by fellow student [[Tom Hooper (director)|Tom Hooper]] in a production of ''[[A View from the Bridge]]'' at the [[Oxford Playhouse]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://awfj.org/2009/09/24/awfj-women-on-film-tom-hooper-on-the-damned-united-jenny-halper-interviews/ |title=AWFJ Women On Film&nbsp;\u2014 Tom Hooper On \"The Damned United\" |accessdate=5 October 2011 |publisher=Alliance of Women Film Journalists |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120305090447/http://awfj.org/2009/09/24/awfj-women-on-film-tom-hooper-on-the-damned-united-jenny-halper-interviews/ |archive-date=5 March 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> As a Modern Languages student, she was required to spend her third year abroad, and studied in Paris. She then decided to quit university to concentrate on her burgeoning acting career: \"It was getting to the point where I wasn't enjoying either thing enough because both were very high pressure.\"<ref name=\"facingup\"/>\n\n==Career==\n===1991\u20131997: Early acting roles===\n[[File:Kate Beckinsale TIFF, 2008.jpg|thumb|left|upright|Beckinsale at the [[2008 Toronto International Film Festival]]]]\nBeckinsale decided at a young age she wanted to be an actress: \"I grew up immersed in film. My family were in the business. I quickly realised that my parents seemed to have much more fun in their work than any of my friends' parents.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.festival-cannes.fr/en/theDailyArticle/57514.html |title=Exclusive Interview with Kate Beckinsale |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=Festival de Cannes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120406013032/http://www.festival-cannes.fr/en/theDailyArticle/57514.html |archive-date=6 April 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> She was inspired by the performances of [[Jeanne Moreau]].<ref name=\"prestigehongkong1\">{{cite web|first=Mathew |last=Scott |url=http://www.prestigehongkong.com/celebrities/010612.html |title=Kate Beckinsale |publisher=Prestige Hong Kong |accessdate=21 August 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120611032231/http://www.prestigehongkong.com/celebrities/010612.html |archivedate=11 June 2012 |df= }}</ref> She made her television debut in 1991 with a small part in an [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] adaptation of [[P. D. James]]' ''[[Devices and Desires]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://movies.amctv.com/movie/257748/Devices-and-Desires/details |title=Devices and Desires |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=AMC |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120406094908/http://movies.amctv.com/movie/257748/Devices-and-Desires/details |archivedate=6 April 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 1992 she starred alongside [[Christopher Eccleston]] in ''Rachel's Dream'', a 30\u2011minute [[Channel 4]] short,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.historyfiles.co.uk/Guide/RachelsDream.htm |title=Rachel's Dream |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=The History Files |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120401230137/http://www.historyfiles.co.uk/Guide/RachelsDream.htm |archive-date=1 April 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> and in 1993, she appeared in the pilot of the [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] detective series, ''[[Anna Lee (TV series)|Anna Lee]]'', starring [[Imogen Stubbs]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tcm.com/tcmdb/title/459624/Anna-Lee-Headcase/ |title=Anna Lee: Headcase |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=Turner Classic Movies |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130602205729/http://www.tcm.com/tcmdb/title/459624/Anna-Lee-Headcase/ |archive-date=2 June 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 1993, Beckinsale landed the role of Hero in [[Kenneth Branagh]]'s big-screen adaptation of ''[[Much Ado About Nothing (1993 film)|Much Ado About Nothing]]''. It was filmed in [[Tuscany]], Italy, during a summer holiday from Oxford University.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://atnzone.com/nz/2008/12/06/interview-kate-beckinsale-gives-\"nothing-but-the-truth\"/ |title=Interview: Kate Beckinsale Gives \"Nothing But The Truth\" |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=N:Zone }}</ref> She attended the film's [[Cannes Film Festival]] premiere and remembered it as an overwhelming experience. \"Nobody even told me I could bring a friend!\"<ref name=\"fear\"/> \"I had [[Doc Martens]] boots on, and I think I put the flower from the breakfast tray in my hair.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://stylenews.peoplestylewatch.com/2010/05/19/kate-beckinsale-cannes-film-festival/ |title=Kate Beckinsale's Red Carpet-Ready Routine |accessdate=6 October 2011 |work=People |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120213184443/http://stylenews.peoplestylewatch.com/2010/05/19/kate-beckinsale-cannes-film-festival/ |archive-date=13 February 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> [[Peter Travers]] of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' was won over by her \"lovely\" performance<ref>{{cite news |title=Much Ado About Nothing |first=Peter |last=Travers |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/reviews/much-ado-about-nothing-19930507 |newspaper=Rolling Stone |date=7 May 1993 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110919040553/http://www.rollingstone.com/movies/reviews/much-ado-about-nothing-19930507 |archive-date=19 September 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> while [[Vincent Canby]] of ''[[The New York Times]]'' noted that she and [[Robert Sean Leonard]] \"look right and behave with a certain naive sincerity, although they often seem numb with surprise at hearing the complex locutions they speak.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=A House Party of Beatrice, Benedick and Friends |first=Vincent |last=Canby |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9F0CE7DD133DF934A35756C0A965958260 |newspaper=The New York Times |date=7 May 1993 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120516133637/http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9F0CE7DD133DF934A35756C0A965958260 |archive-date=16 May 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> The film earned over $22&nbsp;million at the box office.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=muchadoaboutnothing.htm |title=Much Ado About Nothing (1993) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date=27 July 1993 |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110402044018/http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=muchadoaboutnothing.htm |archive-date=2 April 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> She made three other films while at university. In 1994, she appeared as [[Christian Bale]]'s love interest in ''[[Prince of Jutland]]'', a film based on the Danish [[Hamlet (legend)|legend]] which inspired Shakespeare's ''[[Hamlet]]'',<ref>{{cite news |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/133545/Royal-Deceit/overview |title=Royal Deceit |accessdate=6 October 2011 |newspaper=The New York Times |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100323213209/http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/133545/Royal-Deceit/overview |archive-date=23 March 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref> and starred in the murder mystery ''[[Uncovered (film)|Uncovered]]''.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/134226/Uncovered/overview |title=Uncovered |accessdate=6 October 2011 |newspaper=The New York Times |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100827131532/http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/134226/Uncovered/overview |archive-date=27 August 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref> In 1995, while studying in Paris, she filmed the [[French language]] ''Marie-Louise ou la Permission''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinemovies.fr/fiche_film.php?IDfilm=12773 |title=Marie-Louise Ou La Permission |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=Pure Cin\u00e9 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100601125715/http://www.cinemovies.fr/fiche_film.php?IDfilm=12773 |archivedate=1 June 2010 |df= }}</ref>\n\nShortly after leaving Oxford University in 1995, Beckinsale starred in ''[[Cold Comfort Farm (1995 TV film)|Cold Comfort Farm]]'', as Flora Poste, a newly orphaned 1930s socialite sent to live with distant family members in rural England. The [[John Schlesinger]]-directed film was an adaptation of [[Stella Gibbons]]'s [[Cold Comfort Farm|novel]] and also featured [[Joanna Lumley]], [[Eileen Atkins]], [[Ian McKellen]], [[Rufus Sewell]] and [[Stephen Fry]]. Beckinsale was initially considered too young, but was cast after she wrote a pleading letter to the director.<ref name=\"otheremma\">{{cite news |title=The Other Emma Confidently Makes Her Case |first=Sarah |last=Lyall |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/02/16/arts/the-other-emma-confidently-makes-her-case.html?pagewanted=2&src=pm |newspaper=The New York Times |date=16 February 1997 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130906222312/http://www.nytimes.com/1997/02/16/arts/the-other-emma-confidently-makes-her-case.html?pagewanted=2&src=pm |archive-date=6 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Emanuel Levy]] of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' was reminded of \"the strength of a young [[Glenda Jackson]] and the charm of a young [[Julie Christie]].\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Cold Comfort Farm |first=Emanuel |last=Levy |url=https://variety.com/review/VE1117904210 |newspaper=Variety |date=20 June 1995 |accessdate=6 October 2011}}</ref> Kevin Thomas of the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' classed the actress as \"yet another of those effortlessly skilled British beauties who light up the screen.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Inspired Comedy, Charm at 'Cold Comfort Farm' |first=Kevin |last=Thomas |url=https://articles.latimes.com/1996-05-10/entertainment/ca-2695_1_cold-comfort-farm |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=10 May 1996 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120715050744/http://articles.latimes.com/1996-05-10/entertainment/ca-2695_1_cold-comfort-farm |archive-date=15 July 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Janet Maslin]] of ''The New York Times'' felt she played the role \"with the perfect snippy aplomb.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Country Cousins, Feudal And Futile |first=Janet |last=Maslin |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9500E3DA1539F933A25756C0A960958260 |newspaper=The New York Times |date=10 May 1996 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130906225305/http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9500E3DA1539F933A25756C0A960958260 |archive-date=6 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> The film grossed over $5 million at the US box office.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=coldcomfortfarm.htm |title=Cold Comfort Farm (1996) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date=24 May 1996 |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110920175410/http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=coldcomfortfarm.htm |archive-date=20 September 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> Also in 1995, she appeared in ''[[Haunted (1995 film)|Haunted]]'', a ghost story in which Derek Elley of ''Variety'' felt she \"holds the screen, with both physical looks and verbal poise.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Haunted |first=Derek |last=Elley |url=https://variety.com/review/VE1117904684?refcatid=31 |newspaper=Variety |date=13 November 1995 |accessdate=6 October 2011}}</ref> 1995 also saw Beckinsale's first professional stage appearance as Nina in ''[[The Seagull]]'' at [[Theatre Royal, Bath|Theatre Royal]], [[Bath, Somerset|Bath]]. She became romantically involved with co-star [[Michael Sheen]] after meeting during play rehearsals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dealmemo.com/Interview/Kate_Beckinsale_Serendipity.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20020503104355/http://www.dealmemo.com/Interview/Kate_Beckinsale_Serendipity.htm |url-status=dead |archive-date= 3 May 2002 |title=Kate Beckinsale, Serendipity Interview |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=Dealmemo |df= }}</ref> She later said: \"I was all revved up to feel very intimidated. It was my first-ever play and my mother had cut out reviews of him in previous productions. And then he walked in ... It was almost like, 'God, well, I'm finished now. That's it, then.'... He's the most outrageously talented person I've ever met.\"<ref name=\"thisislondon2001\">{{cite news |title=Golden couple from suburbia |first=Jeff |last=Dawson |url=http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/film/article-897397-golden-couple-from-suburbia.do |newspaper=London Evening Standard |date=7 June 2001 |accessdate=6 October 2011}} {{Dead link|date=April 2012|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> [[Irving Wardle]] of ''The Independent'' felt that \"the casting, including Michael Sheen's volcanic Kostya and Kate Beckinsale's steadily freezing Nina, is mainly spot-on.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Even truer West |first=Irving |last=Wardle |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/even-truer-west-1615941.html |newspaper=The Independent |date=16 April 1995 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |location=London |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120906232813/http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/even-truer-west-1615941.html |archive-date=6 September 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> In early 1996, she starred in two further plays; ''Sweetheart'' at the [[Royal Court Theatre]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Theatre Sweetheart Royal Court, London |first=Paul |last=Taylor |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/theatre-sweetheart-royal-court-london-1317556.html |newspaper=The Independent |date=6 February 1996 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120907134842/http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/theatre-sweetheart-royal-court-london-1317556.html |archive-date=7 September 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> and ''Clocks and Whistles'' at [[the Bush Theatre]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Theatre Clocks and Whistles the Bush, London |first=Paul |last=Taylor |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/theatre-clocks-and-whistles-the-bush-london-1302981.html |newspaper=The Independent |date=3 April 1996 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121224175856/http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/theatre-clocks-and-whistles-the-bush-london-1302981.html |archive-date=24 December 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nBeckinsale next starred in an [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] adaptation of [[Jane Austen]]'s ''[[Emma (1996 TV film)|Emma]]'', playing Emma to [[Mark Strong]]'s Mr Knightley and [[Samantha Morton]]'s Harriet Smith. \"You shouldn't necessarily like Emma,\" Beckinsale has said of her character. \"You do love her, but in the way the family of a young girl could be exasperated by her outrageous behaviour and still love her.\"<ref name=\"otheremma\"/> The programme was aired in autumn 1996, just months after [[Gwyneth Paltrow]] had starred in a [[Emma (1996 theatrical film)|film adaptation]] of the same story.<ref name=\"otheremma\"/> Caryn James of ''The New York Times'' felt that while \"Ms.&nbsp;Beckinsale's Emma is plainer looking than Ms.&nbsp;Paltrow's,\" she is \"altogether more believable and funnier.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=An 'Emma' Both Darker And Funnier |first=Caryn |last=James |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/02/15/arts/an-emma-both-darker-and-funnier.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=15 February 1997 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121105222851/http://www.nytimes.com/1997/02/15/arts/an-emma-both-darker-and-funnier.html |archive-date=5 November 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Jonathan Brown of ''The Independent'' has described Beckinsale's interpretation as \"the most enduring modern performance\" as Emma.<ref>{{cite news |title=Has the costume drama had its day? |first=Jonathan |last=Brown |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/media/tv-radio/has-the-costume-drama-had-its-day-1806884.html |newspaper=The Independent |date=22 October 2009 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |location=London |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121104193551/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/media/tv-radio/has-the-costume-drama-had-its-day-1806884.html |archive-date=4 November 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> In 1997, Beckinsale appeared opposite [[Stuart Townsend]] in the comedy ''[[Shooting Fish]]'', one of the most commercially successful British films of that year.<ref>{{cite news |title=British film-maker returns pounds 1m lottery grant as he hits jackpot at box office |first=David |last=Lister |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/british-filmmaker-returns-pounds-1m-lottery-grant-as-he-hits-jackpot-at-box-office-1263989.html |newspaper=The Independent |date=29 May 1997 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |location=London |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120906091611/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/british-filmmaker-returns-pounds-1m-lottery-grant-as-he-hits-jackpot-at-box-office-1263989.html |archive-date=6 September 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=EU presidency fuels push for jobs |first=Paul |last=McCann |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/eu-presidency-fuels-push-for-jobs-1287746.html |newspaper=The Independent |date=9 December 1997 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |location=London |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121224175913/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/eu-presidency-fuels-push-for-jobs-1287746.html |archive-date=24 December 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> \"I'd just had my [[wisdom teeth]] out,\" Beckinsale later recalled of the initial audition. \"I was also on very strong painkillers, so it was not the most conventional of meetings.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Kate beats teeth agony to hook role |first=Brigit |last=Grant |url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/HAMSTER%3b+chops+is+the+tops%3b+Kate+beats+teeth+agony+to+hook+role.-a061055493 |newspaper=The Mirror |date=16 October 1997 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130906021651/http://www.thefreelibrary.com/HAMSTER%3b+chops+is+the+tops%3b+Kate+beats+teeth+agony+to+hook+role.-a061055493 |archive-date=6 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> Elley wrote of \"an incredibly laid-back performance\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Shooting Fish |first=Derek |last=Elley |url=https://variety.com/review/VE1117912099 |newspaper=Variety |date=1 September 1997 |accessdate=6 October 2011}}</ref> while Thomas felt she \"just glows as an aristocrat facing disaster with considerable aplomb.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Caught Up in Overly Complicated 'Fish' |first=Kevin |last=Thomas |url=https://articles.latimes.com/1998/may/01/entertainment/ca-45052 |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=1 May 1998 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110913112720/http://articles.latimes.com/1998/may/01/entertainment/ca-45052 |archive-date=13 September 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> She narrated Austen's ''[[Emma (novel)|Emma]]'' for [[Hodder & Stoughton|Hodder & Stoughton AudioBooks]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.de/Emma-Jane-Austen/dp/1859986234 |title=Emma [Audiobook] |accessdate=11 October 2011 |publisher=Amazon.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130907065707/http://www.amazon.de/Emma-Jane-Austen/dp/1859986234 |archive-date=7 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> and Diana Hendry's ''The Proposal'' for [[BBC Radio 4]].<ref name=\"genome\">{{cite web|url=https://genome.ch.bbc.co.uk/5b4f537cc6944058a5f7b98ec0a6ea9f|title=Short Story: The Proposal|author=BBC Radio 4|date=27 February 1997|website=BBC Genome|accessdate=29 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829072524/https://genome.ch.bbc.co.uk/5b4f537cc6944058a5f7b98ec0a6ea9f|archive-date=29 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldofcelebs.com/ography/kbeckinsalebio.html |title=Kate Beckinsale's Biography |accessdate=11 October 2011 |publisher=World of Celebs |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120425062317/http://www.worldofcelebs.com/ography/kbeckinsalebio.html |archive-date=25 April 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Also in 1997, she played Juliet to [[Michael Sheen]]'s Romeo in an AudioBook<!-- radio? citation needed --> production of ''[[Romeo and Juliet]]'', directed by Sheen.<ref name=\"naxos\">{{cite web |url=http://www.naxosaudiobooks.com/312512.htm |title=Romeo and Juliet (unabridged) |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=Naxos |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110930204354/http://www.naxosaudiobooks.com/312512.htm |archive-date=30 September 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn Beckinsale\u2019s last film before her move to the US, she starred as Alice in [[Channel 4]]\u2019s ''[[Alice through the Looking Glass (1998 film)|Alice through the Looking-Glass]]'', released in July 1998.<ref>Zoe Jaques, Eugene Giddens, Lewis Carroll's ''Alice's Adventures in Wonderland and Through the Looking-Glass: A Publishing History'' (Routledge, 2016), p. 257</ref>\n\n===1998\u20132002: Move to Hollywood===\nAt this point in her career, Beckinsale began to seek work in the United States, something she has said wasn't \"a conscious decision... My boyfriend was in a play on Broadway so that's why we ended up in New York, and my auditions happened to be for American films.\"<ref name=\"bbcserendipity\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/films/2001/12/17/kate_beckinsale_serendipity_interview.shtml |title=Serendipity interview |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=BBC |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130907114555/http://www.bbc.co.uk/films/2001/12/17/kate_beckinsale_serendipity_interview.shtml |archive-date=7 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> She starred opposite [[Chlo\u00eb Sevigny]] in 1998's ''[[The Last Days of Disco]]''. The [[Whit Stillman]] film focused on a group of [[Ivy League]] graduates socialising in the Manhattan disco scene of the early 1980s. Beckinsale's attempt at an American accent was widely praised.<ref>{{cite news |title=The Last Days of Disco |first=Lisa |last=Schwarzbaum |url=https://ew.com/ew/article/0,,283512,00.html |newspaper=Entertainment Weekly |date=5 June 1998 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121009203948/http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,283512,00.html |archive-date=9 October 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Night Life of the Young, Urban and Genteel |first=Janet |last=Maslin |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9C0DE7DE1038F93AA15756C0A96E958260 |work=The New York Times |date=29 May 1998 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927065510/http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9C0DE7DE1038F93AA15756C0A96E958260 |archive-date=27 September 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Disco's Last Dance: Whit Stillman Dips Into the Caldron of Hedonism |first=Stephen |last=Hunter |url=http://www.lastdaysofdisco.com/reviews/washington.html |newspaper=The Washington Post |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110810053044/http://www.lastdaysofdisco.com/reviews/washington.html |archive-date=10 August 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Kenneth Turan]] of the ''Los Angeles Times'' felt her role as the bossy Charlotte was \"beautifully played.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Hearts of Glass at the 'Disco' |first=Kenneth |last=Turan |url=http://www.lastdaysofdisco.com/reviews/latimes.html |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110810053131/http://www.lastdaysofdisco.com/reviews/latimes.html |archive-date=10 August 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Todd McCarthy]] of ''Variety'' was unimpressed by the film but noted that \"compensations include Beckinsale, looking incredible in a succession of black dresses, whose character can get on your nerves even if the actress doesn't.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=The Last Days of Disco |first=Todd |last=McCarthy |url=https://variety.com/review/VE1117477570 |newspaper=Variety |date=25 May 1998 |accessdate=6 October 2011}}</ref> Her performance earned her a [[London Critics Circle Film Awards|London Critics' Circle Film Award]].<ref name=\"talk\"/> The film grossed $3&nbsp;million worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=lastdaysofdisco.htm |title=The Last Days of Disco (1998) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date=26 June 1998 |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121023204456/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=lastdaysofdisco.htm |archive-date=23 October 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 1999, Beckinsale appeared opposite [[Claire Danes]] in ''[[Brokedown Palace]]'', a drama about two young Americans forced to deal with the Thai justice system on a post-graduation trip abroad. A then 26-year-old Beckinsale played a young girl.<ref>{{cite news |title=Shoulda Taken the Summer Job |first=Donald |last=Chase |url=https://articles.latimes.com/1998/may/24/entertainment/ca-52977/4 |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=24 May 1998 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120715013508/http://articles.latimes.com/1998/may/24/entertainment/ca-52977/4 |archive-date=15 July 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Danes had hoped to become friends with Beckinsale during the shoot but found her \"complicated\" and \"prickly.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Hey, Nineteen |first=Christine |last=Spines |url=http://www.clairedanes.com/print/premiere1098.shtml |newspaper=Premiere |date=October 1998 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110623150416/http://www.clairedanes.com/print/premiere1098.shtml |archive-date=23 June 2011 |url-status=dead  }}</ref> McCarthy said the leads \"confirm their status as two of the young actresses on the scene today most worth watching,\" finding Beckinsale \"very effective at getting across layered character traits and emotions.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Brokedown Palace |first=Todd |last=McCarthy |url=https://variety.com/review/VE1117750058?printerfriendly=true |newspaper=Variety |date=12 August 1999 |accessdate=6 October 2011}}</ref> \"Danes and Beckinsale are exceptionally talented young actresses,\" said Thomas, but \"unfortunately, the script's seriously underdeveloped context defeats their considerable efforts at every turn.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Excitement Gets Waylaid in a Trip to 'Brokedown Palace' |first=Kevin |last=Thomas |url=https://articles.latimes.com/1999/aug/13/entertainment/ca-65200 |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=13 August 1999 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120715022709/http://articles.latimes.com/1999/aug/13/entertainment/ca-65200 |archive-date=15 July 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Stephen Holden of ''The New York Times'' felt that Beckinsale's character \"never comes into focus.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=No Pool and No Room Service, Among Other Things |first=Stephen |last=Holden |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9A00EFDB1439F930A2575BC0A96F958260 |newspaper=The New York Times |date=13 August 1999 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110514032250/http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9A00EFDB1439F930A2575BC0A96F958260 |archive-date=14 May 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> The film was a box office failure.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=brokedownpalace.htm |title=Brokedown Palace (1999) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date=28 August 2002 |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120417215810/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=brokedownpalace.htm |archive-date=17 April 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n2000's ''[[The Golden Bowl (film)|The Golden Bowl]]'' marked Beckinsale's first role following the birth of her daughter. The [[Merchant Ivory Productions|Merchant/Ivory]] production was based on the [[The Golden Bowl|novel]] by [[Henry James]] and also starred [[Uma Thurman]] and [[Jeremy Northam]]. Beckinsale's partner, Michael Sheen, hit Northam on the film set after he followed Beckinsale to her trailer to scold her for forgetting a line.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.culture.com/articles/426/pearl-harbor-interview-with-kate-beckinsale.phtml |title=Pearl Harbor interview |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=Culture |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111106173316/http://culture.com/articles/426/pearl-harbor-interview-with-kate-beckinsale.phtml |archive-date=6 November 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> Holden noted \"the most satisfying of the four-lead performances belong to the British cast members, Ms.&nbsp;Beckinsale and Mr.&nbsp;Northam, who are better than their American counterparts at layers of emotional concealment,\" adding each beat of Beckinsale's performance \"registers precisely.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=All the Sensibility That Money Can Buy |first=Stephen |last=Holden |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9C01EFDE1239F934A15757C0A9679C8B63 |newspaper=The New York Times |date=27 April 2001 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130906233934/http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9C01EFDE1239F934A15757C0A9679C8B63 |archive-date=6 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> Thomas felt her performance would take her to \"a new career level.\"<ref>{{cite news |title='Golden Bowl' Is a Gilded Affair |first=Kevin |last=Thomas |url=https://articles.latimes.com/2001/apr/27/entertainment/ca-56235 |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=27 April 2001 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120125130441/http://articles.latimes.com/2001/apr/27/entertainment/ca-56235 |archive-date=25 January 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Andrew Sarris]] of ''[[The New York Observer]]'' asserted that she \"comes close to capturing the sublimity of Maggie, despite the obvious fact that no movie can capture the elegant copiousness of James' prose.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Henry James' Americans Shop for Love and Art Abroad |first=Andrew |last=Sarris |url=http://www.observer.com/2001/04/henry-james-americans-shop-for-love-and-art-abroad/ |newspaper=The New York Observer |date=30 April 2001 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120603234539/http://observer.com/2001/04/henry-james-americans-shop-for-love-and-art-abroad/ |archive-date=3 June 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> The film grossed over $5&nbsp;million worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=goldenbowl.htm |title=The Golden Bowl (2001) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date=28 August 2002 |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120127065414/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=goldenbowl.htm |archive-date=27 January 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nBeckinsale rose to fame in 2001 with a leading role in the war film ''[[Pearl Harbor (film)|Pearl Harbor]]'', as a nurse torn between two pilots (played by [[Ben Affleck]] and [[Josh Hartnett]]). She was drawn to the project by the script: \"It's so unusual these days to read a script that has those old-fashioned values to it. Not morals, but movie values. It's a big, sweeping epic....You just never get the chance to do that.\"<ref name=\"epicturn\">{{cite news |title=An Epic Turn |first=Ellen |last=Baskin |url=https://articles.latimes.com/2001/may/06/entertainment/ca-59782 |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=6 May 2001 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120715033535/http://articles.latimes.com/2001/may/06/entertainment/ca-59782 |archive-date=15 July 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Director [[Michael Bay]] initially had doubts about casting the actress: \"I wasn't sure about her at first...she wore black leather trousers in her screen test and I thought she was a little nasty...it was easy to think of this woman as a slut.\"<ref name=flying>{{cite news |title=No fear of flying |first=Tiffany |last=Rose |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/kate-beckinsale-no-fear-of-flying-754437.html |newspaper=The Independent |date=17 December 2004 |accessdate=14 October 2011 |location=London}}{{dead link|date=November 2011}}</ref> He eventually decided to hire her because she wasn't \"too beautiful. Women feel disturbed when they see someone's too pretty.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.movieline.com/2001/05/michael-bay-bay-watch.php |title=Bay Watch |publisher=Movieline |accessdate=14 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111203080740/http://www.movieline.com/2001/05/michael-bay-bay-watch.php |archivedate=3 December 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He asked her to lose weight during filming.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/forbes/2009/0622/celebrity-09-transformers-michael-bay-making-movies-enemies-money.html |title=Michael Bay: Making Movies, Enemies and Money |date=22 June 2009 |work=Forbes |accessdate=14 October 2011 |first=Dorothy |last=Pomerantz |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160506174434/http://www.forbes.com/forbes/2009/0622/celebrity-09-transformers-michael-bay-making-movies-enemies-money.html |archive-date=6 May 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> In a 2004 interview, the actress noted that his comments were \"upsetting\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.teenhollywood.com/2004/06/03/beckinsale-blasts-insensitive-pearl-harbor-director |title=Beckinsale Blasts Insensitive Pearl Harbor Director |publisher=Teen Hollywood |accessdate=14 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120516101319/http://www.teenhollywood.com/2004/06/03/beckinsale-blasts-insensitive-pearl-harbor-director |archive-date=16 May 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> and said she wore leather trousers because \"it was snowing out. It wasn't exactly like I had my nipple rings in.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=What our 'pearl' Katy did next |first=Lesley |last=O'Toole |url=http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/film/article-561697-what-our-pearl-katy-did-next.do |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130505085025/http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/film/article-561697-what-our-pearl-katy-did-next.do |url-status=dead |archive-date=5 May 2013 |newspaper=London Evening Standard |date=10 December 2004 |accessdate=14 October 2011 }}</ref> She felt grateful that she had not had to deal with such criticism at a younger age: \"If I had come on to a movie set at [a younger] age and someone had said, 'You're a bit funny-looking, can you go on a diet?'\u2014I might have jumped off a building. I just didn't have the confidence to put that into perspective at the time.\"<ref name=flying/> However, speaking in 2011, she said she was \"very fond\" of Bay.<ref>{{cite news |title=Bay directs with tough love |first=David S. |last=Cohen |url=https://variety.com/article/VR1118039080 |newspaper=Variety |date=10 May 2011 |accessdate=14 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110803125534/http://www.variety.com/article/VR1118039080 |archive-date=3 August 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Pearl Harbor'' received negative reviews. [[Owen Gleiberman]] of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' praised \"the avid eyed, ruby lipped Kate Beckinsale, the rare actress whose intelligence gives her a sensual bloom; she's like [[Parker Posey]] without irony.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Pearl Harbor |first=Owen |last=Gleiberman |url=https://ew.com/ew/article/0,,127709,00.html |newspaper=Entertainment Weekly |date=25 May 2001 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110925144158/http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,127709,00.html |archive-date=25 September 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[A.&nbsp;O.&nbsp;Scott]] of ''The New York Times'' noted that \"Mr.&nbsp;Affleck and Ms.&nbsp;Beckinsale do what they can with their lines, and glow with the satiny shine of real movie stars.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=War Is Hell, but Very Pretty |author=A.O. Scott |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9A00E6D7113DF936A15756C0A9679C8B63 |newspaper=The New York Times |date=25 May 2001 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130906220415/http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9A00E6D7113DF936A15756C0A9679C8B63 |archive-date=6 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> However, Mike Clark of ''[[USA Today]]'' felt that the \"usually appealing Kate Beckinsale\" is \"inexplicably submerged&nbsp;\u2014like her hospital colleagues&nbsp;\u2014under heaps of tarty makeup that even actresses of the era didn't wear.\"<ref>{{cite news |title='Pearl Harbor' sputters until Japanese show up |first=Mike |last=Clark |url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/enter/movies/pearl-harbor/2001-05-25-pearl-harbor-review.htm#more |newspaper=USA Today |date=7 June 2001 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110514003829/http://www.usatoday.com/life/enter/movies/pearl-harbor/2001-05-25-pearl-harbor-review.htm#more |archive-date=14 May 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> The film was a commercial success, grossing $449 million worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=pearlharbor.htm |title=Pearl Harbor (2001) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date=22 July 2001 |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714113756/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=pearlharbor.htm |archive-date=14 July 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nBeckinsale's second film appearance of 2001 was in the romantic comedy ''[[Serendipity (film)|Serendipity]]'', as the love interest of [[John Cusack]]. It was filmed directly after ''Pearl Harbor'' and Beckinsale found it \"a real relief to return to something slightly more familiar.\"<ref name=\"bbcserendipity\"/> Turan praised the \"appealing and believable\" leads, adding that Beckinsale \"reinforces the strong impression she made in ''Cold Comfort Farm'', ''The Golden Bowl'', and ''The Last Days of Disco''\" after \"recovering nicely\" from her appearance in the much-maligned ''Pearl Harbor''.<ref>{{cite news |title=A Lightweight Search for Love in 'Serendipity' |first=Kenneth |last=Turan |url=https://articles.latimes.com/2001/oct/05/entertainment/ca-53528 |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=5 October 2001 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120715045653/http://articles.latimes.com/2001/oct/05/entertainment/ca-53528 |archive-date=15 July 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Claudia Puig of ''USA Today'' felt that \"Beckinsale's talents haven't been mined as effectively in any other film since ''Cold Comfort Farm''.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Actors' charms overcome 'Serendipity' snags |first=Claudia |last=Puig |url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/enter/movies/2001-10-05-serendipity-review.htm |newspaper=USA Today |date=4 October 2001 |accessdate=6 October 2011}}</ref> McCarthy found her \"energetic and appealing\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Serendipity |first=Todd |last=McCarthy |url=https://variety.com/review/VE1117798919/ |newspaper=Variety |date=13 September 2001 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121109054617/http://www.variety.com/review/VE1117798919/ |archive-date=9 November 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> while [[Elvis Mitchell]] of ''The New York Times'' described her as \"luminous but determined.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=A Love Made in Heaven (Actually, a Sweet Shop) |first=Elvis |last=Mitchell |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9903E7DD163CF936A35753C1A9679C8B63 |newspaper=The New York Times |date=5 October 2001 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130906230754/http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9903E7DD163CF936A35753C1A9679C8B63 |archive-date=6 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> In an uncomplimentary review of the film, Ebert described her as \"a good actress, but not good enough to play this dumb.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Serendipity |first=Roger |last=Ebert |url=http://rogerebert.suntimes.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20011005/REVIEWS/110050304 |newspaper=Chicago Sun-Times |date=5 October 2001 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111105110131/http://rogerebert.suntimes.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=%2F20011005%2FREVIEWS%2F110050304 |archive-date=5 November 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> The film has grossed over $77 million at the worldwide box office.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=serendipity.htm |title=Serendipity (2001) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date=28 August 2002 |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007063913/http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=serendipity.htm |archive-date=7 October 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2002, Beckinsale starred in [[Lisa Cholodenko]]'s ''[[Laurel Canyon (film)|Laurel Canyon]]'', as a strait-laced academic who finds herself increasingly attracted to her free-spirited future mother-in-law. The independent film was another opportunity for Beckinsale to work with [[Christian Bale]], her ''Prince of Jutland'' co\u2011star. She found their sex scene awkward because she knew Bale well: \"If it was a stranger, it would have been easier.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.askmen.com/celebs/entertainment-news/kate-beckinsale/kate-beckinsale-kissing-confession.html |title=Kate Beckinsale's kissing confession |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=AskMen |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111101223316/http://www.askmen.com/celebs/entertainment-news/kate-beckinsale/kate-beckinsale-kissing-confession.html |archive-date=1 November 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> While [[Frances McDormand]]'s performance as Bale's mother was widely praised, Beckinsale received negative reviews. Holden found the film \"superbly acted, with the exception of Ms.&nbsp;Beckinsale, whose tense, colourless Alex conveys no inner life.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=An Aging Hippie, Making Both Love and War |first=Stephen |last=Holden |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9C05E4DD133FF934A35750C0A9659C8B63 |newspaper=The New York Times |date=7 March 2003 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130906220357/http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9C05E4DD133FF934A35750C0A9659C8B63 |archive-date=6 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> Critic [[Lisa Schwarzbaum]] was unimpressed by the \"tedious\" characters and criticised \"the fussy performances of Bale and Beckinsale\" in particular.<ref>{{cite news |title=Laurel Canyon |first=Lisa |last=Schwarzbaum |url=https://ew.com/ew/article/0,,430000,00.html |newspaper=Entertainment Weekly |date=14 March 2003 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022093901/http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,430000,00.html |archive-date=22 October 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> The film has grossed over $4&nbsp;million worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=laurelcanyon.htm |title=Laurel Canyon (2003) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110819232957/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=laurelcanyon.htm |archive-date=19 August 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===2003\u20132006: Action roles===\n[[File:Kate Beckinsale.jpg|thumb|left|upright|Beckinsale at the 53rd [[San Sebasti\u00e1n International Film Festival]] in 2005]]\nBeckinsale became known as an action star after playing a [[vampire]] in 2003's ''[[Underworld (2003 film)|Underworld]]''. The film was markedly different from her previous work, and Beckinsale has said she was grateful for the change of pace after appearing in \"a bunch of period stuff and then a bunch of romantic comedies,\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://movies.ign.com/articles/437/437658p1.html |title=Underworld's intrepid mistress of the dark |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=IGN |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111011022454/http://movies.ign.com/articles/437/437658p1.html |archive-date=11 October 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> adding that \"It was quite a challenge for me to play an action heroine and pull off all that training when [in real life] I can't catch a ball if it's coming my way.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chud.com/4790/interview-kate-beckinsale-scott-speedman-len-wiseman-underworld-evolution/ |title=Interview with Kate Beckinsale, Len Wiseman and Scott Speedman |date=6 October 2011 |publisher=Chud |access-date=30 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170420110552/http://www.chud.com/4790/interview-kate-beckinsale-scott-speedman-len-wiseman-underworld-evolution/ |archive-date=20 April 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The film received negative to mixed reviews but was a surprise box-office hit and has gained a cult following.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rottentomatoes.com/m/underworld/ |title=Underworld |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111004171948/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/underworld/ |archive-date=4 October 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> Also that year, she starred in the little seen ''[[Tiptoes]]'' with [[Gary Oldman]] and [[Matthew McConaughey]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/300912/Tiptoes/overview |title=Tiptoes |accessdate=6 October 2011 |newspaper=The New York Times |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120507074546/http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/300912/Tiptoes/overview |archive-date=7 May 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 2004, Beckinsale starred in the action [[horror film]] ''[[Van Helsing (film)|Van Helsing]]''. She was \"so surprised\" to be appearing in her second action film in two years. \"It just seemed like a very good role.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://movies.ign.com/articles/510/510829p1.html |title=Star duo tells us what it takes to deliver Van Helsing |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=IGN |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120524195709/http://movies.ign.com/articles/510/510829p1.html |archive-date=24 May 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Beckinsale had just separated from her long-term boyfriend [[Michael Sheen]] at the time of filming and appreciated the warm atmosphere created on set by director [[Stephen Sommers]] and co\u2011star [[Hugh Jackman]]: \"I really did find that working with people like Stephen and Hugh made it possible to get through what I was going through.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.blackfilm.com/20040430/features/vanhelsing.shtml |title=Van Helsing |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=BlackFilm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110805124524/http://www.blackfilm.com/20040430/features/vanhelsing.shtml |archive-date=5 August 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> The film grossed over $120 million at the US box office and over $300 million worldwide, but it was not well-reviewed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rottentomatoes.com/m/van_helsing/ |title=Van Helsing |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111004172013/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/van_helsing/ |archive-date=4 October 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=vanhelsing.htm |title=Van Helsing |accessdate=11 October 2011 |publisher=Box Office Mojo |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111008050023/http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=vanhelsing.htm |archive-date=8 October 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Mick LaSalle]] of the ''[[San Francisco Chronicle]]'' described her as \"a pretty actress doing her best to maintain dignity, vainly trying to craft a feminist statement from a filmmaker's whimsy\"<ref>{{cite news |title='Van Helsing' a monstrosity of a movie |first=Mick |last=LaSalle |url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2004/05/07/DDGGR6G7521.DTL&type=movies |newspaper=The San Francisco Chronicle |date=7 May 2004 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080504043944/http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=%2Fc%2Fa%2F2004%2F05%2F07%2FDDGGR6G7521.DTL&type=movies |archive-date=4 May 2008 |url-status=live }}</ref> while [[Rex Reed]] of ''The New York Observer'' felt she was \"desperately in need of a new agent.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Epic Pecs, Great Effects |first=Rex |last=Reed |url=http://www.observer.com/2004/05/epic-pecs-great-effects/ |newspaper=The New York Observer |date=17 May 2004 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120803160553/http://observer.com/2004/05/epic-pecs-great-effects/ |archive-date=3 August 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAlso in 2004, Beckinsale portrayed [[Ava Gardner]] in [[Martin Scorsese]]'s [[Howard Hughes]] biopic ''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]''. Scorsese decided to cast Beckinsale because, \"I've always liked her. I've seen all her work, and I was glad that she agreed to audition.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://movies.about.com/od/theaviator/a/aviatorms121004_3.htm |title=Interview with Martin Scorsese |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=About |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110915084310/http://movies.about.com/od/theaviator/a/aviatorms121004_3.htm |archive-date=15 September 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> Beckinsale's performance received mixed reviews. [[Ken Tucker]] of ''[[New York Magazine]]'' said she played the part \"in full va-va-voom blossom\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Emperor of the Air |first=Ken |last=Tucker |url=https://nymag.com/nymetro/movies/reviews/10644/ |newspaper=New York |date=21 May 2005 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130906225340/http://nymag.com/nymetro/movies/reviews/10644/ |archive-date=6 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> while LaSalle felt that she manages \"to convince us that Ava was one of the great broads of all time.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Scorsese's 'Aviator' is a sumptuous, entertaining look at the life of Howard Hughes\u2014even if it doesn't have a point |first=Mick |last=LaSalle |url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2004/12/17/DDGFEACEAE1.DTL&type=movies |newspaper=San Francisco Chronicle |date=17 December 2004 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050514071543/http://sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=%2Fc%2Fa%2F2004%2F12%2F17%2FDDGFEACEAE1.DTL&type=movies |archive-date=14 May 2005 |url-status=live }}</ref> However, Clark described it as \"the one performance that doesn't come off (though Beckinsale has the requisite beauty)\"<ref>{{cite news |title='The Aviator' takes off brilliantly and just keeps soaring |first=Mike |last=Clark |url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/movies/reviews/2004-12-16-aviator_x.htm |newspaper=USA Today |date=16 December 2004 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080724115418/http://www.usatoday.com/life/movies/reviews/2004-12-16-aviator_x.htm |archive-date=24 July 2008 |url-status=live }}</ref> while [[Peter Bradshaw]] of ''[[The Guardian]]'' stated that \"Gardner's rich, voluptuous sexiness is completely absent as Beckinsale sleepwalks through the role as if she was advertising perfume.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=The Aviator |first=Peter |last=Bradshaw |url=http://film.guardian.co.uk/News_Story/Critic_Review/Guardian_Film_of_the_week/0,4267,1379282,00.html |newspaper=The Guardian |date=24 December 2004 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |location=London |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111105222811/http://film.guardian.co.uk/News_Story/Critic_Review/Guardian_Film_of_the_week/0,4267,1379282,00.html |archive-date=5 November 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> The film grossed over $213&nbsp;million worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=aviator.htm |title=The Aviator (2004) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111226184209/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=aviator.htm |archive-date=26 December 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 2006, Beckinsale reprised her role as Selene in the successful vampire sequel ''[[Underworld: Evolution]]'', directed by her husband.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?yr=2006&wknd=03&p=.htm |title=January 20\u201322, 2006 Weekend |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=Box Office Mojo |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/65VKu7p1i?url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?yr=2006&wknd=03&p=.htm |archive-date=16 February 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> It was the first time she had \"been involved with a movie from the moment it's a germ of an idea right through the whole editing process.\"<ref name=\"cinecon\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cinecon.com/news.php?id=0601201 |title=Kate Beckinsale on \"Underworld: Evolution\" |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=CineCon |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111208215739/http://www.cinecon.com/news.php?id=0601201 |archive-date=8 December 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> Her daughter had a small role as the younger Selene.<ref name=\"cinecon\"/> The film was a box office success, grossing $111 million worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=underworld2.htm |title=Underworld: Evolution (2006) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date=12 March 2006 |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/65IMbnoEw?url=http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=underworld2.htm |archive-date=8 February 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Beckinsale's second film appearance of 2006 was opposite [[Adam Sandler]] and [[Christopher Walken]] in ''[[Click (2006 film)|Click]]'', a comedy about an overworked family man who discovers a magical remote control that allows him to control time. The opportunity to play a mother \"was one of the things that was attractive to me\" about the part.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wildaboutmovies.com/interviews/KateBeckinsaleClickMovie.php |title=Click interview |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=WildAboutMovies |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111107154158/http://wildaboutmovies.com/interviews/KateBeckinsaleClickMovie.php |archive-date=7 November 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> It was highly profitable, grossing $237&nbsp;million worldwide from a production budget of $82.5&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=click.htm |title=Click (2006) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120519201529/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=click.htm |archive-date=19 May 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===2007\u20132008: Focus on small-scale drama===\nBeckinsale then made a return to smaller-scale projects: \"My experience is that I sort of stepped away from the independent movies and did a couple of big movies. But that's not necessarily how it's perceived by everybody else, which I do understand.\"<ref name=\"aboutnothing\">{{cite web |url=http://movies.about.com/od/nothingbutthetruth/a/kate-beckinsale_2.htm |title=Kate Beckinsale Talks About 'Nothing But the Truth' |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=About |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110911132024/http://movies.about.com/od/nothingbutthetruth/a/kate-beckinsale_2.htm |archive-date=11 September 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> \"I enjoy an action movie as much as the next person [but] it's not something that I would like to do solely.\"<ref name=\"comein\">{{cite web |url=http://www.filmmonthly.com/paul_fischer_exclusive/ms_beckinsale_comes_in_from_the_cold.html |title=Ms. Beckinsale Comes in from the Cold |accessdate=6 October 2011 |work=Film Monthly |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120406222708/http://www.filmmonthly.com/paul_fischer_exclusive/ms_beckinsale_comes_in_from_the_cold.html |archive-date=6 April 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> She explained that she had originally decided to appear in ''Underworld'' because she felt typecast in classical roles&nbsp;\u2014 it was \"assumed that I use a chamber pot and wear bloomers\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Loves & loathes&nbsp;\u2014 Kate Beckinsale |first=Susan |last=Granger |url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Beauty+People%3A+Loves+%26+loathes+-+Kate+Beckinsale%3B+SUSAN+GRANGER...-a075420176 |newspaper=The People |date=10 June 2001 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130906022729/http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Beauty+People%3A+Loves+%26+loathes+-+Kate+Beckinsale%3B+SUSAN+GRANGER...-a075420176 |archive-date=6 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\u2014but that her action career \"kind of took off a little too much.\"<ref name=\"aboutwhiteout\">{{cite web |url=http://movies.about.com/od/whiteout/a/whiteout072808_2.htm |title=Interview with Whiteout Star Kate Beckinsale |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=About.com |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111106112858/http://movies.about.com/od/whiteout/a/whiteout072808_2.htm |archivedate=6 November 2011 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn 2007, Beckinsale starred opposite [[Sam Rockwell]] in the independent drama ''[[Snow Angels (film)|Snow Angels]]'', based on the [[Snow Angels (novel)|novel]] by [[Stewart O'Nan]]. The harrowing film, in which she played an overwhelmed single mother, put Beckinsale \"in kind of a tough place.\" \"I did have my kid, my husband and, in fact, my ex was around a lot, so it was very nice to come home to my people whom I love.\"<ref name=\"comein\"/> Puig felt \"Beckinsale gives her best performance in years\"<ref>{{cite news |title='Snow Angels' lays down a somber tale |first=Claudia |last=Puig |url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/movies/reviews/2008-03-13-snow-angels_N.htm |newspaper=USA Today |date=14 March 2008 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120125073331/http://www.usatoday.com/life/movies/reviews/2008-03-13-snow-angels_N.htm |archive-date=25 January 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> while [[Richard Corliss]] of ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' described it as \"her sharpest work yet.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Snow Angels and Married Life: Wedded Blisters |first=Richard |last=Corliss |url=http://www.time.com/time/arts/article/0,8599,1720367,00.html |newspaper=Time |date=7 March 2008 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111103124051/http://www.time.com/time/arts/article/0,8599,1720367,00.html |archive-date=3 November 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> However, Scott felt that \"her skill and discipline cannot overcome the sense that she is an exotic species transplanted into this grim ecosystem. Hard as she works to convince us otherwise, it's a stretch to believe that a woman with the kind of poised confidence in her own beauty she manifests would wind up with an underachieving mouth breather like Glenn.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Gunshots Underneath a Gray Sky |last=Scott |first=A.&nbsp;O. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/03/07/movies/07snow.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=7 March 2008 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140907031055/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/03/07/movies/07snow.html |archive-date=7 September 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> The film grossed just $414,404 worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=snowangels.htm |title=Snow Angels (2008) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date=2 June 2008 |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120519133648/http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=snowangels.htm |archive-date=19 May 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAlso in 2007, Beckinsale appeared alongside [[Luke Wilson]] in ''[[Vacancy (film)|Vacancy]]'', a thriller set in an isolated motel. [[Sarah Jessica Parker]] was originally cast in the part, but she dropped out before filming began.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mania.com/kate-beckinsale-joins-vacancy_article_52219.html |title=Beckinsale joins Vacancy |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=Mania |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110810224557/http://www.mania.com/kate-beckinsale-joins-vacancy_article_52219.html |archivedate=10 August 2011 |df= }}</ref> Bradshaw felt \"Wilson and Beckinsale have the chops for scary movies\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Vacancy |first=Peter |last=Bradshaw |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2007/jun/15/horror |newspaper=The Guardian |date=15 June 2007 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |location=London |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131221031946/http://www.theguardian.com/film/2007/jun/15/horror |archive-date=21 December 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> while Gleiberman noted \"Luke Wilson, with his hangdog defensive mopiness, and Kate Beckinsale, all sexy severity, are ideally matched as a couple who hate each other.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Vacancy |first=Owen |last=Gleiberman |url=https://ew.com/ew/article/0,,20035189,00.html |newspaper=Entertainment Weekly |date=18 April 2007 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130522215627/http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20035189,00.html |archive-date=22 May 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> However, [[Manohla Dargis]] of ''The New York Times'' was unimpressed, referring to Beckinsale as \"the reigning queen of the bland [[B movie|B]]'s.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Checking in and Not Checking Out |first=Manohla |last=Dargis |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/2007/04/19/movies/20vaca.html?gwh=F6CDE4EE1BC7E538A26BE2B657D216FB |newspaper=The New York Times |date=19 April 2007 |accessdate=6 October 2011}}</ref> The film was profitable, grossing $35&nbsp;million worldwide from a production budget of $19 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=vacancy.htm |title=Vacancy (2007) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date=20 April 2007 |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120519174141/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=vacancy.htm |archive-date=19 May 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n[[Image:KateBeckinsaleJune07.jpg|thumb|upright|Beckinsale at the London premiere of ''[[Live Free or Die Hard]]'' in June 2007]]\nIn 2008, Beckinsale appeared in ''[[Fragments (film)|Winged Creatures]]'', a film about how six different witnesses cope with the aftermath of a shooting. Beckinsale played a [[waitress]]ing single mother in an ensemble cast which included [[Dakota Fanning]], [[Jennifer Hudson]], and [[Forest Whitaker]]. \"It was a really, really nice experience but it was quick,\" said Beckinsale of the filming process. \"I just felt a bit like I was shot through a cannon.\"<ref name=\"comein\"/> Betsy Sharkey of the ''Los Angeles Times'' felt she played the role \"with a [[white trash]] verve\" and found her character's \"raw ache for that someone with money and respectability is palpable.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Its bits and pieces just don't fit |first=Betsy |last=Sharkey |url=https://articles.latimes.com/2009/aug/07/entertainment/et-fragments7 |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=7 August 2009 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120715034814/http://articles.latimes.com/2009/aug/07/entertainment/et-fragments7 |archive-date=15 July 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> However, Dargis felt that Beckinsale and her cast mates have a \"tough time filling out characters that are at best abstractions of grief and often just clich\u00e9s.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Several Points of View on a Single, Cruel Event |first=Manohla |last=Dargis |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/2009/07/31/movies/31fragments.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=30 July 2009 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100830170829/http://movies.nytimes.com/2009/07/31/movies/31fragments.html |archive-date=30 August 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref> The film received a very limited theatrical release in New York and Los Angeles; it was released simultaneously on [[DVD]].<ref>{{cite news | url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/news/peace-arch-release-fragments-friday-87100 | work=The Hollywood Reporter | title=Peace Arch to release 'Fragments' on Friday | date=30 July 2009 | access-date=28 January 2012 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130907011452/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/peace-arch-release-fragments-friday-87100 | archive-date=7 September 2013 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAlso in 2008, Beckinsale starred in ''[[Nothing but the Truth (2008 American film)|Nothing but the Truth]]'', as a journalist who refuses to reveal her source. The film, co\u2011starring [[Vera Farmiga]] and [[Matt Dillon]], was inspired by the case of [[Judith Miller (journalist)|Judith Miller]]. As part of her research for the role, \"I spent some time at ''The L.A. Times'' with some female reporters, and I spoke to Judith Miller about her experience....I really researched the hell out of that one and it was an amazingly fulfilling, brilliant experience.\"<ref name=\"comein\"/> Ann Hornaday of ''The Washington Post'' asserted that Beckinsale and Farmiga played \"two of the most fascinating female movie characters to hit screens in a long while, and they've been brought to life by two gifted actresses, each working at the top of her game.\"<ref>{{cite news |title='Nothing but the Truth' Is Taut, Political Thriller |first=Ann |last=Hornaday |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/04/27/AR2009042703360.html |newspaper=The Washington Post |date=28 April 2009 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101119065254/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/04/27/AR2009042703360.html |archive-date=19 November 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref> Beckinsale received a [[Critic's Choice Award]] nomination for her performance.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bfca.org/ccawards/2008.php |title=The BFCA Critics' Choice Awards: 2008 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=Broadcast Film Critics Association |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101124011333/http://www.bfca.org/ccawards/2008.php |archivedate=24 November 2010 |df= }}</ref> The film never received a full theatrical release after the distributor filed for bankruptcy<ref>{{cite web |url=http://popdose.com/the-popdose-interview-rod-lurie/ |title=The Popdose Interview |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=Popdose |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111226012419/http://popdose.com/the-popdose-interview-rod-lurie/ |archive-date=26 December 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> and the film has grossed just $186,702 worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=nothingbutthetruth08.htm |title=Nothing But the Truth |publisher=Box Office Mojo |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120418040714/http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=nothingbutthetruth08.htm |archive-date=18 April 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> \"I have prayed\u2014''prayed''\u2014for film companies to go [[bankrupt]] on films I've made, and then this happens on the one I love,\" said Beckinsale. \"Usually it's the ones you're most embarrassed about that are on the side of every bus.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=The Great Kate |newspaper=Esquire |date=November 2009 |page=74}}</ref>\n\n===2009\u20132015: Return to action films===\n\nIn 2009, Beckinsale starred in the [[comic-book]] adaption ''[[Whiteout (2009 film)|Whiteout]]'', as a [[United States Marshals Service|US&nbsp;Marshal]] tasked with investigating a murder in Antarctica. It was filmed in [[Manitoba]], Canada.<ref name=\"aboutwhiteout\"/> She found the action scenes less physically demanding than those in ''Underworld'' because \"three pairs of trousers and a parka gives you a bit more protection than the [[latex]] suit.\"<ref name=\"aboutwhiteout\"/> The film was critically panned and a box office failure, failing to recoup its budget.<ref name=\"whiteout\">{{cite web |url=https://rottentomatoes.com/m/10008655-whiteout/ |title=Whiteout |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110930001719/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/10008655-whiteout/ |archive-date=30 September 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> With critics consensus: Beckinsale is the lovely as ever, and does her best with the material, but moribund pacing and an uninspired plot leave Whiteout in the cold.<ref name=\"whiteout\"/> She also made a brief cameo in the prequel ''[[Underworld: Rise of the Lycans]]''; she appeared in [[flashforward]]s composed of footage from 2003's ''Underworld''.<ref name=\"filmstalker1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.filmstalker.co.uk/archives/2009/01/beckinsale_is_in_underworld_3.html |title=Beckinsale is in Underworld 3 |accessdate=11 October 2011 |publisher=Film Stalker |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120330152535/http://www.filmstalker.co.uk/archives/2009/01/beckinsale_is_in_underworld_3.html |archive-date=30 March 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Also in 2009, Beckinsale starred in the family drama ''[[Everybody's Fine (2009 film)|Everybody's Fine]]'' alongside [[Robert De Niro]], [[Drew Barrymore]], and Rockwell, her ''Snow Angels'' co-star. Beckinsale was excited by the opportunity to work with De Niro, whom she had first encountered \"years and years ago when I just had Lily and he was putting together a reading of ''[[The Good Shepherd (film)|The Good Shepherd]]''.\".<ref name=\"aboutnothing\"/> ''Everybody's Fine'' was a box office flop, failing to recoup its production budget.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=everybodysfine09.htm |title=Everybody's Fine (2009) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date=24 December 2009 |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100607134619/http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=everybodysfine09.htm |archive-date=7 June 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref> In May 2010, Beckinsale sat on the nine-member [[2010 Cannes Film Festival]] jury, chaired by director [[Tim Burton]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://huffingtonpost.com/2010/05/22/tim-burton-kate-beckinsal_n_585886.html |title=Tim Burton, Kate Beckinsale, Benicio del Toro And Cannes Jury Get To Work |date=22 May 2010 |work=HuffPost |accessdate=21 December 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130406152254/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2010/05/22/tim-burton-kate-beckinsal_n_585886.html |archive-date=6 April 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> Unable to find a script she felt passionate about, Beckinsale kept a low profile in 2010 and 2011, opting to spend time with her daughter.<ref name=ballroom>{{cite web|first=Maxwell |last=Williams |url=http://flaunt.com/features/118/kate-beckinsale-revolving-ballroom-sea |title=Kate Beckinsale in the Revolving Ballroom by the Sea |work=Flaunt|accessdate=21 January 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120103094401/http://flaunt.com/features/118/kate-beckinsale-revolving-ballroom-sea |archivedate= 3 January 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\nBeckinsale returned to acting in 2012 with appearances in three action films. Beckinsale first appeared in the action thriller ''[[Contraband (2012 film)|Contraband]]''. She had a supporting role as the wife of [[Mark Wahlberg]]'s character, a former criminal who gets forced back into a life of crime after his family members are threatened. The film was directed by [[Baltasar Korm\u00e1kur]], who also starred in the [[Icelandic language]] version of the film, ''[[Reykjav\u00edk-Rotterdam]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://empireonline.com/news/story.asp?NID=32109 |title=Trailer For Contraband Hits Online |accessdate=6 October 2011 |work=Empire |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111027130652/http://www.empireonline.com/news/story.asp?NID=32109 |archive-date=27 October 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> The ''San Francisco Chronicle'' felt Beckinsale was \"stuck in a bit of a thankless role as the victimised wife, but she does try to infuse a harder edge to the character.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/n/a/2012/01/11/national/a125113S27.DTL |title=Review: Wahlberg does one last job in `Contraband' |first=Christy |last=Lemire |date=11 January 2012 |work=San Francisco Chronicle |accessdate=17 January 2012 }}{{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> ''The Hollywood Reporter'' stated that \"Beckinsale, her innate classiness calibrated down a few notches, has little to do but be supportive, worried and, eventually, besieged.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/review/contraband-review-mark-wahlberg-280621|title=Contraband: Film Review|first=Todd|last=McCarthy|date=11 January 2012|work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=17 January 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120115002255/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/contraband-review-mark-wahlberg-280621|archive-date=15 January 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> ''Entertainment Weekly'' felt that the \"woman-in-peril stuff is second-rate, giving off a whiff of exploitation\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://ew.com/ew/article/0,,20483133_20556653,00.html|title=Contraband (2012)|first=Owen|last=Gleiberman|date=12 January 2012|work=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=17 January 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120115002854/http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20483133_20556653,00.html|archive-date=15 January 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> while ''Variety'' found the repeated violence towards Beckinsale's character disturbing.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/review/VE1117946821?refcatid=31|title=Contraband|first=Justin|last=Chang|date=11 January 2012|work=Variety|accessdate=17 January 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120118091236/http://www.variety.com/review/VE1117946821?refcatid=31|archive-date=18 January 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> The film had a production budget of $25&nbsp;million and has grossed over $96&nbsp;million worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=contraband.htm |title=Contraband (2012) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120310084608/http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=contraband.htm |archive-date=10 March 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nBeckinsale next reprised her role as Selene in the fourth instalment of the vampire franchise ''[[Underworld: Awakening]]''.<ref name=\"filmstalker1\"/> The franchise was initially conceived of as a trilogy and Beckinsale was not \"intending to do another one\" but was convinced by the quality of the script.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://collider.com/kate-beckinsale-underworld-4-awakening-interview/109777/ |title=Beckinsale |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=Collider |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110823210823/http://collider.com/kate-beckinsale-underworld-4-awakening-interview/109777/ |archive-date=23 August 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''The Hollywood Reporter'' noted that \"when she's not actually fighting, her performance consists of little more than striding purposefully toward or away from the camera.\"<ref>{{cite news | url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/review/underworld-awakening-review-kate-beckinsale-283605 | work=The Hollywood Reporter | first=Frank | last=Scheck | title=Underworld: Awakening: Film Review | access-date=28 January 2012 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120123035928/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/underworld-awakening-review-kate-beckinsale-283605 | archive-date=23 January 2012 | url-status=live }}</ref> The ''Los Angeles Times'' remarked that she \"finally manages to perfect the monotone delivery she'd been honing for the series' first two entries.\"<ref>{{cite news| url=https://latimes.com/entertainment/news/movies/la-et-underworld-awakening-20120123,0,54079.story?track=rss | work=Los Angeles Times | first=Glenn | last=Whipp | title=Movie review: 'Underworld: Awakening' | date=23 January 2012}}</ref> The film had a production budget of $70 million and has grossed over $160 million worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=underworld4.htm |title=Underworld Awakening (2012) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6ChMpplre?url=http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=underworld4.htm |archive-date=6 December 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://boxofficemojo.com/people/chart/?id=katebeckinsale.htm|title=Kate Beckinsale Movie Box Office Results|publisher=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110606185112/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/people/chart/?id=katebeckinsale.htm|archive-date=6 June 2011|url-status=live}}</ref> Also in 2012, Beckinsale appeared as the wife of a factory worker in the sci-fi action remake ''[[Total Recall (2012 film)|Total Recall]]'', directed by her husband Len Wiseman.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://empireonline.com/news/story.asp?NID=31644 |title=Exclusive: Colin Farrell On Total Recall |accessdate=6 October 2011 |work=Empire |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111106213848/http://www.empireonline.com/news/story.asp?NID=31644 |archive-date=6 November 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> She has said Wiseman joined the project because he was unable to receive studio financing for an original sci-fi idea: \"You're constantly finding yourself having to defend doing a remake when you didn't really want to make one in the first place.\"<ref name=ballroom/> The film received mainly negative reviews.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rottentomatoes.com/m/total_recall_2010/ |title=Total Recall |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |date=5 August 2012 |accessdate=21 August 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120812151440/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/total_recall_2010/ |archive-date=12 August 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Variety'' found her performance \"one-note\" while ''The Hollywood Reporter'' described her as \"one-dimensional.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Chang |first=Justin |url=https://variety.com/review/VE1117947985?refcatid=31 |title=Variety Reviews \u2013 Total Recall \u2013 Film Reviews \u2013 New U.S. Release \u2013 Review by Justin Chang |work=Variety |date=1 August 2012 |accessdate=21 August 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120807142525/http://www.variety.com/review/VE1117947985?refcatid=31 |archive-date=7 August 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/review/total-recall-film-review-colin-farrell-357781 |title=Total Recall: Film Review |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=8 February 2012 |accessdate=21 August 2012 |first=Justin |last=Lowe |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120904071459/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/total-recall-film-review-colin-farrell-357781 |archive-date=4 September 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''USA Today'' remarked she \"spends much of the movie strutting down hallways and looking relentlessly, though blandly, nasty.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/movies/reviews/story/2012-08-03/total-recall-colin-farrell-kate-beckinsale-jessica-biel/56720862/1?csp=34life |title=Rebel against this relentless 'Total Recall' remake |work=USA Today |date= 2 August 2012|accessdate=21 August 2012}}</ref> The ''New York Post'' asserted Beckinsale \"vastly overstays her welcome.\"<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nypost.com/p/entertainment/movies/total_recoil_nfbehr1NMDgULWVeiupeTJ |title=Colin Farrell doesn't have a shot at living up to Arnold Schwarzenegger in regrettable remake of 'Total Recall' |work=New York Post |date=2 August 2012 |accessdate=21 August 2012 |first=Kyle |last=Smith |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120805215337/http://www.nypost.com/p/entertainment/movies/total_recoil_nfbehr1NMDgULWVeiupeTJ |archive-date=5 August 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The film has grossed $198 million from a production budget of over $125&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=totalrecall2012.htm |title=Total Recall (2012) (2012) |publisher=Box Office Mojo |date=3 August 2012 |accessdate=21 August 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120903110651/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=totalrecall2012.htm |archive-date=3 September 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Barnes |first=Brooks |url=http://artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/08/05/total-recall-remake-struggles-at-box-office/ |title='Total Recall' Remake Struggles at Box Office |publisher=Artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com |date=5 August 2012 |accessdate=21 August 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120815185911/http://artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/08/05/total-recall-remake-struggles-at-box-office/ |archive-date=15 August 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, Beckinsale starred in the legal thriller ''[[The Trials of Cate McCall]]'' opposite [[Nick Nolte]] and [[James Cromwell]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Fleming |first=Mike |url=https://deadline.com/2012/05/cate-beckinsale-nick-nolte-start-work-on-the-trials-of-cate-mccall/ |title=Kate Beckinsale, Nick Nolte Start Work On 'The Trials of Cate McCall' |publisher=Deadline Hollywood |date=21 February 2012 |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120519081341/http://www.deadline.com/2012/05/cate-beckinsale-nick-nolte-start-work-on-the-trials-of-cate-mccall/ |archive-date=19 May 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> The film received negative reviews and was released as a [[LMN (TV channel)|Lifetime]] movie.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crushable.com/2014/04/06/entertainment/lifetime-movie-the-trials-of-cate-mccall-review/|title=The Only 10 Entertaining Moments In Lifetime Movie The Trials Of Cate McCall|publisher=Crushable|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160707084327/http://www.crushable.com/2014/04/06/entertainment/lifetime-movie-the-trials-of-cate-mccall-review/|archive-date=7 July 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/kate-benckinsale-film-flop-trials-3092037|title=Kate Beckinsale film flop The Trials of Cate McCall makes embarrassing \u00a3728.51 - in HUNGARY|first=Hannah|last=Hope|date=30 January 2014|newspaper=The Mirror|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160707014303/http://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/kate-benckinsale-film-flop-trials-3092037|archive-date=7 July 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> She next appeared in the little-seen psychological thriller ''[[Stonehearst Asylum]]'', loosely based on [[Edgar Allan Poe]]'s [[The System of Doctor Tarr and Professor Fether|short story]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deadline.com/2013/04/millennium-adds-michael-caine-ben-kingsley-jim-sturgess-to-eliza-graves|title=Millennium Adds Michael Caine, Ben Kingsley, Jim Sturgess To 'Eliza Graves'|first=Mike Jr|last=Fleming|date=12 April 2013|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131020032800/http://www.deadline.com/2013/04/millennium-adds-michael-caine-ben-kingsley-jim-sturgess-to-eliza-graves/|archive-date=20 October 2013|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/jim-sturgess-star-opposite-kate-432347|title=Jim Sturgess to Star Opposite Kate Beckinsale in 'Eliza Graves' (Exclusive)|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160131010613/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/jim-sturgess-star-opposite-kate-432347|archive-date=31 January 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> A lukewarm critical reception greeted the film upon its DVD release; Jeannette Catsoulis of ''The New York Times'' said Beckinsale was \"emoting as if an Oscar nomination depended on it\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/10/24/movies/stonehearst-asylum-stars-ben-kingsley-and-kate-beckinsale.html|title=Caution: This Institution Processes Nuts|date=24 October 2014|work=The New York Times|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160709091059/http://www.nytimes.com/2014/10/24/movies/stonehearst-asylum-stars-ben-kingsley-and-kate-beckinsale.html|archive-date=9 July 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> while Dennis Harvey of ''Variety'' found her performance \"overwrought.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/reviews/film-review-stonehearst-asylum-1201331213/|title=Film Review: 'Stonehearst Asylum'|first=Dennis|last=Harvey|date=16 October 2014|work=Variety|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160503110838/http://variety.com/2014/film/reviews/film-review-stonehearst-asylum-1201331213/|archive-date=3 May 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2014, she provided the voice for Queen Ayrenn, a character in ''[[The Elder Scrolls Online]]'' video game.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/gaming/news/a546202/john-cleese-bill-nighy-join-elder-scrolls-online-cast-video.html|title=Cleese, Nighy cast in Elder Scrolls Online|date=23 January 2014|work=Digital Spy|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924050033/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/gaming/news/a546202/john-cleese-bill-nighy-join-elder-scrolls-online-cast-video.html|archive-date=24 September 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> Also in 2014, Beckinsale starred in the psychological thriller ''[[The Face of an Angel]]'' alongside [[Daniel Br\u00fchl]]. The film, directed by [[Michael Winterbottom]], was inspired by the case of [[Meredith Kercher]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deadline.com/2013/10/kate-beckinsale-joins-michael-winterbottoms-the-face-of-an-angel/|title=Kate Beckinsale Joins Michael Winterbottom's 'The Face Of An Angel'|first=Mike Jr|last=Fleming|date=15 October 2013|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140419214311/http://www.deadline.com/2013/10/kate-beckinsale-joins-michael-winterbottoms-the-face-of-an-angel/|archive-date=19 April 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> Jesse Hassenger of ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' felt her \"charismatic\" performance was wasted.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://avclub.com/review/michael-winterbottom-tackles-amanda-knox-case-face-220569|title=Michael Winterbottom tackles the Amanda Knox case with The Face Of An Angel|date=18 June 2015|publisher=The A.V. Club|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160515185636/http://www.avclub.com/review/michael-winterbottom-tackles-amanda-knox-case-face-220569|archive-date=15 May 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Also that year, she starred alongside [[Simon Pegg]] in the poorly received British comedy ''[[Absolutely Anything]]'', as an author agency employee and the love interest of a man (Pegg) chosen by four aliens to do anything he wants.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deadline.com/2014/02/kate-beckinsale-joins-simon-pegg-monty-python-troupe-for-absolutely-anything/|title=Kate Beckinsale Joins Simon Pegg, Monty Python Troupe For 'Absolutely Anything'|first=Nancy|last=Tartaglione|date=26 February 2014|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140705063201/http://www.deadline.com/2014/02/kate-beckinsale-joins-simon-pegg-monty-python-troupe-for-absolutely-anything/|archive-date=5 July 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> Tom Huddleston of ''[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out]]'' said her character \"is never really developed\u2014which is perhaps a blessing, because her cut-glass-posh performance is almost as grating as Pegg's.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timeout.com/london/film/absolutely-anything|title=Absolutely Anything|work=Time Out|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613155328/http://www.timeout.com/london/film/absolutely-anything|archive-date=13 June 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> A fan of [[Monty Python]] growing up, in 2014 Beckinsale appeared on the fourth episode of ''Monty Python's Best Bits (Mostly)'' where she spoke of her favourite Python comedy sketch.<ref>{{cite news |title=Monty Python's Best Bits (Mostly) |url=https://www.radiotimes.com/tv-programme/e/c7nmqn/monty-pythons-best-bits-mostly--series-1-episode-4/ |accessdate=5 September 2019 |work=Radio Times}}</ref>\n\n===2016\u2013present: ''Love & Friendship'' and onwards===\n[[File:Kate Beckinsale (29907748884) (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Beckinsale in 2016]]\nIn the 2016 romantic comedy ''[[Love & Friendship]]'', which premiered at the [[Sundance Film Festival]], Beckinsale reunited with her ''Last Days of Disco'' collaborators Stillman and Sevigny. Based on [[Jane Austen]]'s ''[[Lady Susan]]'', the film revolved around her role as the title character, a wry and calculating widow, as she pursues a wealthy and hapless man for marriage originally intended for her daughter, though she eventually marries him herself. The film was universally acclaimed by critics<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/love-friendship|title=Love & Friendship|publisher=Metacritic|access-date=22 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170603150937/http://www.metacritic.com/movie/love-friendship|archive-date=3 June 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> and found commercial success in [[Art film|arthouse cinemas]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=lovefriendship.htm|title=Love & Friendship (2016)|publisher=Box Office Mojo|access-date=22 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170531213726/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=lovefriendship.htm|archive-date=31 May 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Justin Chang]] of ''Variety'' described the role as \"one of the most satisfying screen roles of her career[...] Beckinsale magnetizes the screen in a way that naturally underscores how far ahead of everyone else she is: an effect that doesn't always work to the movie's advantage.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/festivals/love-and-friendship-review-sundance-jane-austen-1201687362/|title=Sundance Film Review: 'Love & Friendship'|first=Justin|last=Chang|date=24 January 2016|work=Variety|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160530051137/http://variety.com/2016/film/festivals/love-and-friendship-review-sundance-jane-austen-1201687362/|archive-date=30 May 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Todd McCarthy of ''The Hollywood Reporter'' remarked, \"There aren't great depths to the role, but Beckinsale excels with the long speeches and in defining her character as a very self-aware egoist.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/review/love-friendship-sundance-review-858759|title='Love & Friendship': Sundance Review|work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320091539/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/love-friendship-sundance-review-858759|archive-date=20 March 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAlso in the year, she starred in the horror film ''[[The Disappointments Room]]'', opposite [[Mel Raido]], both playing a couple in a new house that contains a hidden room with a haunted past. The film was heavily panned by critics and flopped at the box office;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_disappointments_room/|title=The Disappointments Room|publisher=Rotten Tomatoes|access-date=22 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171127120301/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_disappointments_room|archive-date=27 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> it only made US$1.4 million in its opening weekend, and a total of US$2.4 million in North America.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=disappointmentsroom.htm|title=The Disappointments Room (2016)|publisher=Box Office Mojo|access-date=22 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170510000656/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=disappointmentsroom.htm|archive-date=10 May 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Christian Holub of ''Entertainment Weekly'' concluded that \"[m]ost of the film is just Beckinsale walking around looking worried\",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2016/09/09/disappointments-room-ew-review/|title='The Disappointments Room': EW review|work=Entertainment Weekly|access-date=22 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170509065821/http://ew.com/article/2016/09/09/disappointments-room-ew-review/|archive-date=9 May 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> while Joe Leydon of ''Variety'' found her \"credible and compelling [...] except for when she's trying way too hard in a rather unfortunate scene that calls for drunken ranting.\"<ref>{{cite web |first=Joe |last=Leydon |url=https://variety.com/2016/film/reviews/the-disappointments-room-reviews-1201857437/ |title='The Disappointments Room' Review: Some Movie Titles Are Just Too Easy |work=Variety |date=12 September 2016 |accessdate=24 April 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170512064418/http://variety.com/2016/film/reviews/the-disappointments-room-reviews-1201857437/ |archive-date=12 May 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> In late 2016, Beckinsale returned as Selene in the fifth installment of the ''Underworld'' franchise, ''[[Underworld: Blood Wars]]'', which grossed US$81.1 million worldwide.<ref>Stephan Lee. Entertainment Weekly, 22 January 2016, pp. 56\u201357.</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://thewrap.com/love-friendship-review-whit-stillman-kate-beckinsale-chloe-sevigny-jane-austen/ |title=Alonso Duralde, ''The Wrap'', 24 January 2016 |access-date=25 January 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160130021442/http://www.thewrap.com/love-friendship-review-whit-stillman-kate-beckinsale-chloe-sevigny-jane-austen/ |archive-date=30 January 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nBeckinsale starred opposite [[Pierce Brosnan]], [[Callum Turner]], and [[Jeff Bridges]] in [[Marc Webb]]'s romantic coming-of-age drama ''[[The Only Living Boy in New York (film)|The Only Living Boy in New York]]'' (2017),<ref>{{cite web |first=Dave |last=McNary |url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/kate-beckinsale-only-living-boy-in-new-york-1201866055/ |title=Kate Beckinsale Joins 'Only Living Boy in New York' |work=Variety |date=20 September 2016 |accessdate=24 April 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170619160655/http://variety.com/2016/film/news/kate-beckinsale-only-living-boy-in-new-york-1201866055/ |archive-date=19 June 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> as a book editor and the mistress of a publisher whose son sees his life upended. Reviews for the film were mediocre, while it found a limited audience in theaters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_only_living_boy_in_new_york|title=The Only Living Boy in New York|publisher=Rotten Tomatoes|access-date=29 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171127151411/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_only_living_boy_in_new_york/|archive-date=27 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> ''The A.V. Club'' found Brosnan and Beckinsale to be \"vastly more interesting by the twin virtues of not disguising their voices and fitting so poorly into the sad-faced melodrama this movie wants to be\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://film.avclub.com/the-only-living-boy-in-new-york-is-a-simon-garfunkel-1798193396|title=The Only Living Boy In New York is a Simon & Garfunkel song brought to life and made terrible|first=Jesse|last=Hassenger|website=The A.V. Club|access-date=29 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180530035446/https://film.avclub.com/the-only-living-boy-in-new-york-is-a-simon-garfunkel-1798193396|archive-date=30 May 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> She is attached to star in an adaptation of ''The Chocolate Money'' by Ashley Prentice Norton,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tracking-board.com/exclusive-kate-beckinsale-to-produce-adaptation-of-coming-of-age-novel-the-chocolate-money/|title={Exclusive} Kate Beckinsale To Produce Adaptation Of Coming-Of-Age Novel \"The Chocolate Money\"|date=6 January 2016|publisher=tracking-board.com|accessdate=3 June 2016}}</ref> with a screenplay by [[Emma Forrest]].<ref>{{cite web |first=Dave |last=McNary |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/adam-shankman-kate-beckinsale-chocolate-money-1201971534/ |title=Adam Shankman to Direct Kate Beckinsale in 'Chocolate Money' |work=Variety |date=27 January 2017 |accessdate=24 April 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170411054428/http://variety.com/2017/film/news/adam-shankman-kate-beckinsale-chocolate-money-1201971534/ |archive-date=11 April 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Beckinsale starred in the [[ITV (TV channel)|ITV]]/[[Amazon Prime]] drama ''[[The Widow (TV series)|The Widow]]'', her first TV series for more than 20 years.<ref name=\"The Widow\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/01/kate-beckinsale-star-the-widow-drama-series-amazon-itv-1202234376/|title=Kate Beckinsale To Star In \u2018The Widow\u2019 Drama Series For Amazon & ITV|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=3 January 2018|website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=3 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180103162827/http://deadline.com/2018/01/kate-beckinsale-star-the-widow-drama-series-amazon-itv-1202234376/|archive-date=3 January 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The series stars Beckinsale as an Englishwoman who believes her husband, killed in a plane crash three years prior, is still alive in the Congo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/kate-beckinsale-the-widow-amazon-1202650989/|title=Amazon and ITV Greenlight \u2018The Widow,\u2019 Starring Kate Beckinsale|first=Danielle|last=Turchiano|date=3 January 2018|work=Variety|access-date=14 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190714115803/https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/kate-beckinsale-the-widow-amazon-1202650989/|archive-date=14 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbcamerica.com/anglophenia/2018/01/kate-beckinsale-set-to-star-in-the-widow-tv-series-on-amazon-and-itv|title=Kate Beckinsale Set to Star in \u2018The Widow\u2019 TV Series on Amazon and ITV|first=Brigid|last=Brown|website=BBC America|access-date=14 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416031927/http://www.bbcamerica.com/anglophenia/2018/01/kate-beckinsale-set-to-star-in-the-widow-tv-series-on-amazon-and-itv|archive-date=16 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Modeling career===\nBeckinsale has worked occasionally as a model. In 1997, she appeared in the [[music video]] for [[George Michael]]'s \"[[Waltz Away Dreaming]]\".<ref name=\"talk\">{{cite web |url=http://www.talktalk.co.uk/entertainment/film/biography/artist/kate-beckinsale/biography/66?page=4 |title=Kate Beckinsale: Biography |accessdate=11 October 2011 |publisher=Talk Talk |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121004083455/http://www.talktalk.co.uk/entertainment/film/biography/artist/kate-beckinsale/biography/66?page=4 |archive-date=4 October 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> She starred opposite [[Orlando Bloom]] in a 2002 [[Gap (clothing retailer)|Gap]] [[television advertisement]] directed by [[Cameron Crowe]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/1953004.stm |title=Top directors plug the Gap |publisher=BBC |date=26 April 2002 |accessdate=11 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130907162938/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/1953004.stm |archive-date=7 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> She appeared in a [[Diet Coke]] television advertisement in 2004, directed by [[Michael Gondry]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2004/05/27/beckinsales-coke-break |title=Beckinsale's Coke Break |accessdate=11 October 2011 |work=Vogue |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120802000311/http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2004/05/27/beckinsales-coke-break |archive-date=2 August 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bevnet.com/news/newswire/2004/05-05-2004-dietcoke_newgraph.asp/ |title=Diet Coke Unveils 'Effervescent' New Ad Campaign and Graphics |accessdate=11 October 2011 |publisher=Bevnet |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130907015318/http://www.bevnet.com/news/newswire/2004/05-05-2004-dietcoke_newgraph.asp/ |archive-date=7 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> She advertised [[Absolut Vodka]] in a 2009 print campaign photographed by [[Ellen von Unwerth]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://huffingtonpost.com/2009/12/03/kate-beckinsale-zooey-des_n_378895.html |title=Kate Beckinsale & Zooey Deschanel's Sexy Absolut Ads |accessdate=11 October 2011 |work=HuffPost |first=Katherine |last=Thomson |date=3 December 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110907174437/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/12/03/kate-beckinsale-zooey-des_n_378895.html |archive-date=7 September 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Absolut Adds Star Power |url=http://mediadecoder.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/12/01/absolut-adds-star-power/ |newspaper=The New York Times |date=1 December 2009 |accessdate=11 October 2011 |first=Stuart |last=Elliott |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711101327/http://mediadecoder.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/12/01/absolut-adds-star-power/ |archive-date=11 July 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> She has also promoted [[Lux (soap)|Lux]] shampoo in a Japanese television advertisement.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.heart.co.uk/photos/celebrity-ads-they-dont-want-you-see/ |title=Celebrity ads they don't want you to see |accessdate=11 October 2011 |publisher=Heart |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120407050233/http://www.heart.co.uk/photos/celebrity-ads-they-dont-want-you-see/ |archive-date=7 April 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n\n===Relationships===\nBeckinsale had an eight-year relationship with actor [[Michael Sheen]] from 1995 until 2003. They met when cast in a touring production of ''The Seagull'' in early 1995 and moved in together shortly afterwards.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Happy+discoveries+intrigue+Kate%3B+FILM%3A+Beckinsale+pleased+with+Pearl...-a080999324 |title=Happy discoveries intrigue Kate |first=Rob |last=Driscoll |date=21 December 2001 |newspaper=The Western Mail |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025074917/http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Happy+discoveries+intrigue+Kate%3B+FILM:+Beckinsale+pleased+with+Pearl...-a080999324 |archive-date=25 October 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iofilm.co.uk/feats/interviews/k/kate_beckinsale.shtml |title=That's Serendipity |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=Film Inside Out |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160323185705/http://www.iofilm.co.uk/feats/interviews/k/kate_beckinsale.shtml |archivedate=23 March 2016 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"Iley\">{{cite news|first=Chrissey|last=Illey|title=Kate Beckinsale on her gritty new roles|url=http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/film/article6732240.ece|date=2 September 2009|accessdate=6 October 2011|newspaper=The Times|location=London}}</ref> In 1997, they [[voice acting|voiced]] an audiobook<!-- radio? {{citation needed|date=October 2017}} --> production of ''Romeo and Juliet''.<ref name=\"naxos\"/> Their daughter, Lily, was born in [[London]] in 1999.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hellomagazine.com/celebrities/2017020136300/kate-beckinsale-celebrates-daughter-lily-18th-birthday/|title=Kate Beckinsale celebrates daughter Lily\u2019s 18th birthday|date=1 February 2017|website=HELLO!|access-date=6 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190506162346/https://www.hellomagazine.com/celebrities/2017020136300/kate-beckinsale-celebrates-daughter-lily-18th-birthday/|archive-date=6 May 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2001, the actress said she was \"embarrassed\" that Sheen never proposed,<ref name=\"thisislondon2001\"/><ref>{{cite news |title=Kate Beckinsale keeps dropping hints, but still her lover won't tie knot |first=Gill |last=Pringle |url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/WHY+I+AM+STILL+NOT+MARRIED%3b+Kate+Beckinsale+keeps+dropping+hints%2c+but...-a080557085 |newspaper=Daily Record |date=5 December 2001 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130906050903/http://www.thefreelibrary.com/WHY+I+AM+STILL+NOT+MARRIED%3b+Kate+Beckinsale+keeps+dropping+hints%2c+but...-a080557085 |archive-date=6 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> but felt as though she was married.<ref>{{cite news|title=Loves & loathes&nbsp;\u2014 Kate Beckinsale |first=Susan |last=Granger |url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Beauty+People%3a+Loves+%26+loathes+-+Kate+Beckinsale%3b+SUSAN+GRANGER...-a075420176 |newspaper=The People |date=10 June 2001 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130906022729/http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Beauty+People%3A+Loves+%26+loathes+-+Kate+Beckinsale%3B+SUSAN+GRANGER...-a075420176 |archive-date=6 September 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref> Their relationship ended in early 2003, after the filming of ''Underworld''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news.nsf/article/beckinsale%20proud%20wiseman%20and%20sheen%20get%20along_1072222 |title=Beckinsale 'Proud' Wiseman and Sheen Get Along |publisher=Contact Music |date=23 June 2008 |accessdate=6 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090408060324/http://www.contactmusic.com/news.nsf/article/beckinsale%20proud%20wiseman%20and%20sheen%20get%20along_1072222 |archive-date=8 April 2009 |url-status=live }}</ref> Beckinsale and Sheen remain close friends. She remarked in 2016: \"He's really dear, close family. He's somebody I've known since I was 21 years old. I really love him a lot.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=si6xIZkmjHI|title=Kate Beckinsale on 'Love and Friendship'|last=Popcorn with Peter Travers|date=25 May 2016|via=YouTube|accessdate=3 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180808144622/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=si6xIZkmjHI|archive-date=8 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBeckinsale met director [[Len Wiseman]] on the set of 2003's ''Underworld''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com.au/celebrity/news/kate-beckinsale-has-split-from-her-husband-of-11-years/news-story/96c043bd4d5d2d8223803243c3d3a3fe|title=Kate Beckinsale has split from her husband of 11 years - Vogue Australia|first=Julia|last=Frank|website=vogue.com.au|accessdate=29 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829073830/https://www.vogue.com.au/celebrity/news/kate-beckinsale-has-split-from-her-husband-of-11-years/news-story/96c043bd4d5d2d8223803243c3d3a3fe|archive-date=29 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Beckinsale persuaded Wiseman to cast Sheen in the film,<ref name=\"ign\">{{cite web |url=http://movies.ign.com/articles/437/437658p3.html |title=An Interview with Kate Beckinsale |accessdate=6 October 2011 |publisher=IGN |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090207091032/http://movies.ign.com/articles/437/437658p3.html |archive-date=7 February 2009 |url-status=live }}</ref> but while on set, she and Wiseman fell in love. Wiseman\u2019s then-wife Dana, a kindergarten teacher, claimed infidelity in [[Budapest]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.contactmusic.com/new/xmlfeed.nsf/story/beckinsale-branded-home.wrecker |title=Kate Beckinsale Branded Home-Wrecker |publisher=Contactmusic.com |accessdate=19 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130505004104/http://www.contactmusic.com/news-article/beckinsale-branded-home.wrecker |archive-date=5 May 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> Beckinsale and Wiseman deny getting together while ''Underworld'' was shooting.<ref name=\"nypost.com\">{{cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2012/07/29/love-kate-relationship/|title=Love Kate relationship|date=29 July 2012|website=New York Post|accessdate=29 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829072658/https://nypost.com/2012/07/29/love-kate-relationship/|archive-date=29 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> They married on 9 May 2004 in [[Bel Air, Los Angeles|Bel-Air, California]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/3702833.stm |title=Beckinsale marries in US ceremony |publisher=BBC |accessdate=28 October 2010 |date=11 May 2004 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120128074145/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/3702833.stm |archive-date=28 January 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Beckinsale and Wiseman announced their separation in November 2015, and Wiseman filed for divorce in 2016, citing \"irreconcilable differences\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/717505/kate-beckinsale-and-husband-len-wiseman-separate-after-11-years-of-marriage|title=Kate Beckinsale and Husband Len Wiseman Separate After 11 Years of Marriage|last=Bacardi|first=Francesca|publisher=[[E!]]|date=20 November 2015|accessdate=21 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Kate Beckinsale Husband Len Wiseman Files For Divorce|url=https://tmz.com/2016/10/25/kate-beckinsale-divorce-len-wiseman/|work=TMZ|date=25 October 2016|accessdate=2 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170104180232/http://www.tmz.com/2016/10/25/kate-beckinsale-divorce-len-wiseman/|archive-date=4 January 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> As of November 2019, their divorce was finalized.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/kate-beckinsale-len-wiseman-finalize-divorce-4-years-after-split/|title=Kate Beckinsale and Len Wiseman Finalize Divorce 4 Years After Split|last=Hautman|first=Nicholas|work=[[Us Weekly]]|date=5 November 2019|accessdate=8 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2019, Beckinsale was reported to be dating the American comedian [[Pete Davidson]], but by April they had \u201ccalled time on their romance\u201d.<ref>Natasha Sporn, \u201cKate Beckinsale and Pete Davidson 'split after a few months of dating'\u201d in [[London Evening Standard]] dated Friday 26 April 2019, p. 5</ref>\n\n===Personal and political beliefs===\nBeckinsale is a [[Chain smoking|smoker]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/en/beauty/beauty-news/2010/05/kate-beckinsale-|title=Kate Beckinsale|website=Vogue|accessdate=29 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829110053/https://www.vogue.it/en/beauty/beauty-news/2010/05/kate-beckinsale-|archive-date=29 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> When she was nine, her mother moved in with [[Roy Battersby]], and his sons introduced her to [[cigarette]]s.<ref name=\"dad-confused-with-God\">{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/starsandstories/3655308/I-used-to-get-my-dad-confused-with-God.html|title=I used to get my dad confused with God|first=John|last=Hiscock|date=15 September 2006|newspaper=The Telegraph|accessdate=29 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829072513/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/starsandstories/3655308/I-used-to-get-my-dad-confused-with-God.html|archive-date=29 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> She [[Teetotalism|does not drink alcohol]].<ref name=\"ign.com\">{{cite web|url=https://ign.com/articles/2003/09/11/an-interview-with-kate-beckinsale?page=3|title=An Interview with Kate Beckinsale|date=10 September 2003|website=IGN|accessdate=29 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180904083147/http://www.ign.com/articles/2003/09/11/an-interview-with-kate-beckinsale?page=3|archive-date=4 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<blockquote>\"...I've never been drunk even. I've never taken drugs. I've never had a one-night-stand....\"<ref name=\"ign.com\"/></blockquote>\n\nIn 2007, she appeared alongside [[David Schwimmer]] in the sixth of the Writers Guild of America member-conceived Internet videos for Project \"Speechless\", in support of the [[2007\u201308 Writers Guild of America strike|WGA labour strike against the Alliance of Motion Picture & Television Producers]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2007/11/speechless-episode-6-david-schwimmer-and-kate-beckinsale-directed-by-rod-lurie-4073/|title=\"Speechless\" Episode #6: David Schwimmer and Kate Beckinsale|first=Nikki|last=Finke|date=23 November 2007|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=4 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171212031445/https://deadline.com/2007/11/speechless-episode-6-david-schwimmer-and-kate-beckinsale-directed-by-rod-lurie-4073/|archive-date=12 December 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.funnyordie.com/videos/bda8af8327/david-schwimmer-and-kate-beckinsale-speechless-from-speechlesshollywood|title=David Schwimmer and Kate Beckinsale. Speechless.|publisher=Funny or Die|access-date=4 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171016134808/http://www.funnyordie.com/videos/bda8af8327/david-schwimmer-and-kate-beckinsale-speechless-from-speechlesshollywood|archive-date=16 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, she appeared alongside [[Judy Greer]] and [[Andrea Savage]] in the [[Funny or Die]] video \"Republicans, Get in My Vagina\", a satire of the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]]'s policies concerning [[abortion]] and [[pre-natal care]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/funny-or-die-republicans-get-my-vagina-kate-beckinsale-judy-greer-320888|title='Republicans, Get in My Vagina': Kate Beckinsale, Judy Greer and Andrea Savage Post Funny or Die Satire (Video)|work=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=31 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170401144522/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/funny-or-die-republicans-get-my-vagina-kate-beckinsale-judy-greer-320888|archive-date=1 April 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Legal actions===\nIn July 2003, the [[Press Complaints Commission]] dismissed a complaint filed by Beckinsale. Beckinsale had claimed that the ''[[Daily Mail]]'' invaded her and her daughter's privacy by publishing photographs of the actress embracing and kissing her then new boyfriend [[Len Wiseman]].<ref name=autogenerated3>{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2003/jul/31/dailymail.pressandpublishing | location=London | work=The Guardian | first=Ciar | last=Byrne | title=Mail did not invade Beckinsale's privacy | date=31 July 2003 | access-date=12 December 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160524101919/http://www.theguardian.com/media/2003/jul/31/dailymail.pressandpublishing | archive-date=24 May 2016 | url-status=live }}</ref> The article was headlined \"Mummy's latest love scene leaves Lily unimpressed\" and included a picture in which her four-year-old daughter appeared to be ignoring her mother's romantic actions.<ref name=autogenerated3 /> The Commission found that \"the photographs had been taken in a public place and did not reveal any private details about Lily\u2014such as her health or schooling\u2014but were restricted to general observations about her apparent reaction to her surroundings.\"<ref name=autogenerated3 />\n\nIn August 2003, Beckinsale received a published apology from the ''[[Daily Mail]]'' after the newspaper reported that she had \"spent time in a clinic\" following her split from boyfriend [[Michael Sheen]].<ref name=autogenerated2>{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2003/aug/22/dailymail.pressandpublishing?INTCMP=ILCNETTXT3487 | location=London | work=The Guardian | first=Ciar | last=Byrne | title=Mail apologises to Pearl Harbor star | date=22 August 2003 | access-date=12 December 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310063033/http://www.theguardian.com/media/2003/aug/22/dailymail.pressandpublishing?INTCMP=ILCNETTXT3487 | archive-date=10 March 2016 | url-status=live }}</ref> The apology was issued after the actress filed a complaint with the Press Complaints Commission.<ref name=autogenerated2 /> In 2009, Beckinsale was awarded \u00a320,000 in damages by the British [[High Court of Justice|High Court]] after taking legal action against ''[[Express Newspapers]]''.<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2009/jul/09/daily-express-kate-beckinsale|location=London|work=The Guardian|first=Oliver|last=Luft|title=Daily Express makes \u00a320,000 libel payout to Kate Beckinsale|date=9 July 2009|access-date=12 December 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160722084414/https://www.theguardian.com/media/2009/jul/09/daily-express-kate-beckinsale|archive-date=22 July 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> The ''[[Daily Express]]'' had falsely reported that the actress was \"facing heartbreak\" after missing out on a role in a remake of ''[[Barbarella (film)|Barbarella]]''.<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n\n===Charity work===\nThe [[British Heart Foundation]] has been Beckinsale's charity of choice \"ever since [she] was six years old\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gettyimages.com/detail/video/kate-beckinsale-on-being-a-part-of-the-evening-who-her-news-footage/83792404 |title='The 2nd Annual CNN Heroes: An All-Star Tribute'' (2008) News |accessdate=13 October 2011 |publisher=Getty |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326050522/http://www.gettyimages.com/detail/video/kate-beckinsale-on-being-a-part-of-the-evening-who-her-news-footage/83792404 |archive-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.looktothestars.org/charity/british-heart-foundation|title=British Heart Foundation: Celebrity Supporters|website=Look to the Stars|accessdate=30 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830073931/https://www.looktothestars.org/charity/british-heart-foundation|archive-date=30 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> when her father, who had a congenital heart defect, died of a massive heart attack. She has also donated film memorabilia to the [[Epidermolysis Bullosa]] Medical Research Foundation,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.looktothestars.org/celebrity/kate-beckinsale|title=Kate Beckinsale: Charity Work & Causes|website=Look to the Stars|accessdate=30 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830074101/https://www.looktothestars.org/celebrity/kate-beckinsale|archive-date=30 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.looktothestars.org/news/641-courteney-cox-and-david-arquette-in-a-race-for-research |title=Courteney Cox and David Arquette in a Race for Research |accessdate=13 October 2011 |publisher=Look to the Stars |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110905074439/http://www.looktothestars.org/news/641-courteney-cox-and-david-arquette-in-a-race-for-research |archive-date=5 September 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[MediCinema]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.looktothestars.org/news/2032-stars-heal-patients-with-a-kiss |title=Stars Heal Patients with a Kiss |accessdate=13 October 2011 |publisher=Look to the Stars |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120407055829/http://www.looktothestars.org/news/2032-stars-heal-patients-with-a-kiss |archive-date=7 April 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Habitat For Humanity]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.looktothestars.org/news/2103-stars-sign-hardhats-for-charity-auction |title=Stars Sign Hardhats For Charity Auction |accessdate=13 October 2011 |publisher=Look to the Stars |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120407055857/http://www.looktothestars.org/news/2103-stars-sign-hardhats-for-charity-auction |archive-date=7 April 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> and the [[Entertainment Industry Foundation]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.looktothestars.org/news/1955-slip-into-kate-beckinsales-cat-suit-for-charity |title=Slip Into Kate Beckinsale's Cat Suit For Charity |accessdate=13 October 2011 |publisher=Look to the Stars |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120407055907/http://www.looktothestars.org/news/1955-slip-into-kate-beckinsales-cat-suit-for-charity |archive-date=7 April 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2008, she hosted the 4th Annual Pink Party to raise funds for the Women's Cancer Research Institute at [[Cedars-Sinai Medical Center]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.instyle.com/instyle/package/general/photos/0,,20223895_20225811_20509525,00.html |title=Stars who give back: Jennifer Garner and Kate Beckinsale |accessdate=13 October 2011 |publisher=InStyle |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100520070645/http://www.instyle.com/instyle/package/general/photos/0,,20223895_20225811_20509525,00.html |archive-date=20 May 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref> and organised a screening of ''[[All About Eve]]'' for [[FilmAid International]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/online/daily/2008/10/filmaid-screening |title=Watching Movies for a Good Cause |accessdate=13 October 2011 |work=Vanity Fair |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120115015240/http://www.vanityfair.com/online/daily/2008/10/filmaid-screening |archive-date=15 January 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2012, Beckinsale joined [[Nestl\u00e9]]'s Share the Joy of Reading Program to raise awareness about the importance of people's literacy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marketwatch.com/story/kate-beckinsale-teams-up-with-the-nestle-share-the-joy-of-reading-program-during-national-reading-month-to-raise-awareness-about-people's-literacy-2012-03-01|title=Kate Beckinsale Teams Up With \"The Nestl\u00e9 Share the Joy of Reading Program\" During National Reading Month to Raise Awareness About People's Literacy|publisher=MarketWatch|accessdate=19 May 2012}}{{Dead link|date=July 2018|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[Much Ado About Nothing (1993 film)|Much Ado About Nothing]]''\n| Hero\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1994\n| ''[[Prince of Jutland]]''\n| Ethel\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Uncovered (film)|Uncovered]]''\n| Julia\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1995\n| ''[[Cold Comfort Farm (film)|Cold Comfort Farm]]''\n| Flora Poste\n|\n|-\n| ''Marie-Louise ou la Permission''\n| Marie-Louise\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Haunted (1995 film)|Haunted]]''\n| Christina Mariell\n|\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''[[Emma (1996 TV film)|Emma]]''\n| [[Emma Woodhouse]]\n|\n|-\n| 1997\n| ''[[Shooting Fish]]''\n| Georgie\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|1998\n| ''[[The Last Days of Disco]]''\n| Charlotte Pingress\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Alice through the Looking Glass (1998 film)|Alice through the Looking Glass]]''\n| [[Alice (Alice's Adventures in Wonderland)|Alice]]\n|\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[Brokedown Palace]]''\n| Darlene Davis\n|\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''[[The Golden Bowl (film)|The Golden Bowl]]''\n| Maggie Verver\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2001\n| ''[[Pearl Harbor (film)|Pearl Harbor]]''\n| Nurse Lt. Evelyn Johnson\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Serendipity (film)|Serendipity]]''\n| Sara Thomas\n|\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Laurel Canyon (film)|Laurel Canyon]]''\n| Alex Elliot\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2003\n| ''[[Underworld (2003 film)|Underworld]]''\n| [[Selene (Underworld)|Selene]]\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Tiptoes]]''\n| Carol\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2004\n| ''[[Van Helsing (film)|Van Helsing]]''\n| [[Anna Valerious]]\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Van Helsing: The London Assignment]]''\n| [[Queen Victoria]]\n| Voice\n|-\n| ''[[The Aviator (2004 film)|The Aviator]]''\n| [[Ava Gardner]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2006\n| ''[[Underworld: Evolution]]''\n| [[Selene (Underworld)|Selene]]\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Click (2006 film)|Click]]''\n| Donna Newman\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2007\n| ''[[Snow Angels (film)|Snow Angels]]''\n| Annie Marchand\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Vacancy (film)|Vacancy]]''\n| Amy Fox\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2008\n| ''[[Winged Creatures (film)|Winged Creatures]]''\n| Carla Davenport\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Nothing but the Truth (2008 American film)|Nothing but the Truth]]''\n| Rachel Armstrong\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Vacancy 2: The First 